gain-4520180%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParliament%20Panel%20May%20Tell%20Government%20To%20Criminalise%20Adultery%20Again%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20P%20Chidambaram%20was%20among%20those%20who%20submitted%20dissent%20notes%3B%20%26quot%3B...%20the%20State%20has%20no%20business%20to%20enter%20into%20the%20lives%20of%20a%20couple%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20as%20he%20raised%20three%20%26quot%3Bfundamental%20objections%26quot%3B%20that%20included%20claims%20that%20all%20three%20bills%20are%20%26quot%3Blargely%20a%20copy%20and%20paste%20of%20the%20existing%20laws%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20led%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20said%20adultery%20%26quot%3Bcan%20be%20a%20ground%20for%20a%20civil%20offence...%20for%20divorce...%26quot%3B%20but%20could%20not%20be%20a%20criminal%20offence.%20The%20court%20reasoned%20that%20the%20163-year-old%2C%20colonial-era%20law%20followed%20the%20invalidated%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bhusband%20is%20master%20of%20the%20wife%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20scathing%20comments%2C%20the%20court%20called%20the%20law%20%26quot%3Barchaic%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3Barbitrary%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpaternalistic%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20said%20it%20infringed%20on%20a%20woman's%20autonomy%20and%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fadultery-law-is-arbitrary-says-chief-justice-dents-the-individuality-of-women-1922922%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdultery%20Not%20A%20Crime%2C%20%26quot%3BHusband%20Not%20Master%20of%20Wife%2C%26quot%3B%20Says%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government's%20attempt%20at%20overhauling%20the%20IPC%2C%20the%20CrPC%20and%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20are%20part%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20oft-repeated%20statement%20about%20freeing%20India%20from%20colonial-era%20laws.%20In%20September%20this%20year%20and%20in%20October%20last%20year%20the%20PM%20spoke%20about%20the%20need%20for%20%26quot%3Bcontemporary%20laws%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%202018%20verdict%2C%20the%20law%20said%20a%20man%20who%20had%20sex%20with%20a%20married%20woman%20-%20without%20her%20husband's%20consent%20-%20could%20face%20a%20five-year%20sentence%20if%20convicted.%20The%20woman%20would%20not%20be%20punished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs'%20report%20wants%20the%20adultery%20law%20brought%20back%20with%20that%20bit%20struck%20down%3B%20this%20means%20the%20man%20and%20the%20woman%20will%20both%20face%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20has%20also%20asked%20that%20%26quot%3Bnon-consensual%26quot%3B%20sex%20acts%20-%20as%20once%20defined%20in%20the%20partly%20struck-down%20Section%20377%2C%20another%20a%20British-era%20law%2C%20this%20time%20criminalising%20homosexuality%20-%20be%20penalised%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20377%20was%20partially%20junked%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20also%20in%202018.%20The%20ban%20is%20irrational%2C%20indefensible%20and%20manifestly%20arbitrary%2C%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20Misra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhomosexuality-no-longer-a-crime-in-india-supreme-court-ends-controversial-section-377-1912202%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELove%2C%20Equally%3A%20Homosexuality%20No%20Longer%20A%20Crime%2C%20Says%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20panel%20has%20now%20claimed%20that%20though%20the%20court%20found%20the%20struck-down%20parts%20violated%20Articles%2014%2C%2015%2C%2019%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20those%20%26quot%3Bremain%20applicable%20in%20cases%20of%20non-consensual%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20adults%2C%20all%20acts%20of%20carnal%20intercourse%20with%20minors%2C%20and%20acts%20of%20bestiality%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20now%2C%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20no%20provision%20for%20non-consensual%20sexual%20offences%20against%20male%2C%20female%2C%20transgender%20and%20for%20bestiality%20has%20been%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20panel%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20its%20major%20'overhaul'%20of%20India's%20criminal%20laws%2C%20the%20government%20is%20looking%20at%20changing%20punishments%20for%20those%20guilty%20of%20gang-rapes%20(20%20years%20to%20life)%20and%20killing%20minors%20(the%20death%20penalty).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20big%20proposed%20changes%20are%20a%2012-month%20jail%20term%20for%20those%20guilty%20of%20bribing%20voters%20during%20elections%2C%20and%20new%20offences%20in%20existing%20laws%20on%20secession%2C%20armed%20rebellion%2C%20subversive%20and%2For%20separatist%20activities%2C%20and%20endangering%20the%20sovereignty%20or%20unity%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699964520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fe7uafvb_old-and-new-parliament_625x300_20_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbharatiya-nyan-sanhita-adultery-a-crime-again-4573340%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Adultery%20should%20be%20made%20a%20crime%20again%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20institution%20of%20marriage%20is%20sacred%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20must%20be%20%26quot%3Bprotected%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20parliamentary%20panel%20recommended%20to%20the%20government%20Tuesday%20in%20its%20report%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyay%20Sanhita.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbharatiya-nyan-sanhita-adultery-a-crime-again-4573340%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbharatiya-nyan-sanhita-adultery-a-crime-again-4573340%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.co