%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20certain%20weapons%20conventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20includes%20what%20is%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fwar-and-law%2Ftreaties-customary-law%2Fcustomary-law%5C%22%3Ecustomary%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20rules%20that%20are%20accepted%20by%20states%20are%20legally%20binding%2C%20but%20are%20not%20necessarily%20part%20of%20any%20formal%20treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimply%20put%2C%20these%20instruments%20seek%20to%20spare%20civilians%20and%20others%20who%20are%20no%20longer%20active%20combatants%20from%20the%20effects%20of%20hostilities%20by%20placing%20restrictions%20and%20prohibitions%20on%20the%20conduct%20of%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20that%20modern%20IHL%20is%20not%20concerned%20with%20the%20reasons%20for%2C%20or%20the%20legality%20of%2C%20going%20to%20war.%20Rather%2C%20that%20is%20governed%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fabout-us%2Fun-charter%2Ffull-text%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Charter%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20member%20states%E2%80%99%20own%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20important%20to%20note%20that%20violations%20of%20the%20laws%20of%20war%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2022%2F03%2F22%2Frussia-putin-war-crimes-icc-ukraine%5C%22%3Enotoriously%20hard%20to%20prosecute%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20can%20be%20frustrated%20by%20lack%20of%20cooperation%20by%20the%20parties%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FlyBMVriOKIk%3Fsi%3DVmecQ_cyIc3Tqd6E%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20civilian%20structures%20ever%20be%20lawfully%20attacked%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20IHL%2C%20civilian%20objects%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20homes%2C%20apartment%20blocks%2C%20hospitals%20and%20schools%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fwhen-are-attacks-civilian-infrastructure-war-crimes-2022-12-16%2F%5C%22%3Ecannot%20be%20directly%20attacked%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20because%20they%2C%20unlike%20munitions%20factories%20and%20command%20and%20control%20centres%2C%20do%20not%20effectively%20contribute%20to%20military%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20caveat%2C%20however.%20If%20enemy%20forces%20take%20up%20positions%20in%20these%20civilian%20structures%2C%20then%20they%20become%20military%20objectives%20and%20can%20be%20lawfully%20bombed%20if%20the%20raid%20would%20yield%20the%20attacking%20party%20a%20definite%20military%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20stipulation%20does%20not%20allow%20unlimited%20license%20to%20attack%20such%20structures.%20The%20civilians%20located%20in%20those%20buildings%20are%20not%20lawful%20targets.%20As%20such%2C%20they%20retain%20the%20benefits%20of%20what%20is%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flieber.westpoint.edu%2Fproportionality-international-humanitarian-law-principle-rule%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20rule%20of%20proportionality%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20relates%20to%20collateral%20civilian%20casualties%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20deaths%20that%20are%20not%20intended%20by%20the%20attacking%20party%20but%20nonetheless%20result%20from%20their%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20exactly%20is%20the%20rule%20of%20proportionality%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20of%20proportionality%20applies%20to%20all%20armed%20conflicts%20as%20part%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fwar-and-law%2Ftreaties-customary-law%2Fcustomary-law%5C%22%3Ecustomary%20IHL%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proportionality%20rule%20operates%20as%20a%20general%20restraint%20on%20the%20conduct%20of%20parties%20engaged%20in%20hostilities%20and%20applies%20to%20attacks%20against%20lawful%20military%20targets%20located%20in%20the%20vicinity%20of%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20prohibits%20an%20attack%20that%20may%20be%20expected%20to%20cause%20incidental%20death%20or%20injury%20to%20civilians%20or%20the%20destruction%20of%20civilian%20objects%20that%20would%20be%20excessive%20%E2%80%93%20or%20disproportionate%20%E2%80%93%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20concrete%20and%20direct%20military%20advantage%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01125649%2FUNI448902.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22770%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01125649%2FUNI448902.jpeg%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01125649%2FUNI448902-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682898%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22513%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAmal%2C%20seven%20years%20old%2C%20contemplates%20her%20neighbourhood%20in%20Gaza%20after%20neighbouring%20homes%20were%20levelled%20to%20the%20ground.%20Photo%3A%20UNICEF%2FMohammad%20Ajjour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20rule%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20enemy%20combatants%20or%20civilians%20who%20are%20directly%20participating%20in%20hostilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proportionality%20rule%20requires%20those%20who%20plan%20a%20military%20operation%20to%20undertake%20in%20good%20faith%20a%20pre-attack%20analysis%20to%20determine%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20attack%20on%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20determination%20requires%20a%20balancing%20of%20probabilities%20that%20take%20in%20foreseeable%20collateral%20civilian%20casualties%20and%20the%20relative%20importance%20of%20a%20particular%20military%20target.%20This%20is%20a%20relational%20concept%20%E2%80%93%20in%20other%20words%2C%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20quantified%20by%20stating%20any%20fixed%20number%20of%20civilians%20dead%20or%20injured%20for%20any%20one%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20uncertainties%20of%20warfare%2C%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20civilian%20casualties%20may%20be%20greater%20or%20less%20than%20what%20the%20pre-attack%20analysis%20predicted.%20So%20too%20might%20the%20military%20advantage%20gained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20lawfulness%20of%20such%20an%20attack%20must%20be%20based%20on%20an%20honest%20appreciation%20of%20the%20facts%20and%20circumstances%20known%20to%20military%20planners%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20not%20in%20hindsight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20planners%20of%20a%20particular%20attack%20must%20choose%20a%20weapon%20that%20ideally%20will%20avoid%20or%20minimise%20likely%20civilian%20collateral%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20planners%20of%20any%20attack%20must%20suspend%20or%20cancel%20the%20operation%20if%20it%20becomes%20apparent%20that%20the%20target%20selected%20is%20not%20a%20military%20objective%2C%20or%20if%20the%20attack%20will%20result%20in%20disproportionate%20collateral%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20rule%20or%20proportionality%20requires%20the%20attacking%20party%20to%20place%20high%20priority%20on%20the%20timely%20collection%20and%20evaluation%20of%20target%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fd1lszSfhgKg%3Fsi%3DbK9jPIC_dsNMSKGf%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20the%20rule%20of%20proportionality%20be