2allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fk5B1684GWJY%3Fsi%3Dcv0mDIo3siFeOaM6%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20continued%20the%20Middle%20East%20policy%20of%20Trump%20and%20took%20it%20to%20another%20level%20by%20trying%20to%20normalise%20relations%20between%20two%20hitherto%20implacable%20adversaries%20%E2%80%93%20Israel%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20a%20fear%20of%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20growing%20assertiveness%20also%20drove%20the%20Arab%20countries%20towards%20establishing%20friendly%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20These%20policy%20shifts%20inevitably%20meant%20backing%20away%20from%20their%20traditional%20position%20on%20Palestine%20and%20aligned%20well%20with%20US%20policy%20towards%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20the%20hopes%20and%20aspiration%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20turned%20to%20outrage%2C%20anger%20and%20despair.%20They%20were%20ignored%2C%20and%20the%20eruption%20of%20that%20anger%20is%20now%20all%20too%20evident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israel-Hamas%20war%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20not%20really%20the%20%E2%80%98black-swan%E2%80%99%20event%20some%20have%20made%20it%20out%20to%20be.%20And%20its%20tremors%20now%20threaten%20to%20shift%20the%20tectonic%20plates%20of%20geopolitics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20only%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20also%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20basic%20assumption%20of%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20could%20be%20peace%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20without%20addressing%20the%20Palestinian%20question%20%E2%80%93%20has%20come%20unstuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20Arab-Israel%20normalisation%20is%20in%20tatters.%20Even%20those%20Arab%20countries%20that%20sought%20to%20normalise%20ties%20with%20Israel%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20back%20off%20and%20criticise%20Tel%20Aviv.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20countries%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20today%20largely%20stand%20with%20the%20Palestinians.%20Most%20of%20them%20voted%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98humanitarian%20pause%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20fighting%20in%20Gaza%20in%20a%20resolution%20passed%20by%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%2C%20with%20121%20countries%20voting%20in%20favour%20and%2014%20against%2C%20with%2044%20abstentions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20a%20dozen%20countries%2C%20including%20South%20Africa%2C%20have%20withdrawn%20ambassadors%20or%20all%20their%20diplomats%20from%20Israel%2C%20in%20protest%20against%20its%20violence%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurprisingly%2C%20the%20Global%20South%20stands%20with%20Russia%20and%20China%20against%20the%20US-led%20pro-Israeli%20geopolitical%20formation%2C%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20its%20condemnation%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20This%20could%20pose%20serious%20long-term%20threats%20to%20US%20strategic%20goals%20not%20only%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20but%20also%20in%20Africa%20and%20the%20Asia-Pacific%2C%20where%20it%20seeks%20to%20contain%20the%20influence%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20countries%20like%20India%20which%20were%20historically%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20espousing%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20are%20today%20unwilling%20to%20make%20Israel%20uneasy%20by%20condemning%20its%20actions%20in%20Gaza.%20Although%20the%20final%20contours%20remain%20hazy%2C%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20is%20clearly%20reshaping%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ci%3Eoriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%5C%22%3E360info%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A169995