%20KKR%3B%20the%20other%20worked%20at%20Goldman.%20Where%20would%20you%20rather%20be%20now%2C%20the%20KKR%20guy%20asked%20with%20a%20laugh.%20At%20a%20heavily%20regulated%20bank%20like%20Goldman%3F%20Or%20at%20a%20private-equity%20firm%2C%20where%20you%20can%20do%20anything%20you'd%20like%2C%20and%20make%20multiples%20more%20money%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Goldman%20guy%20laughed%20too%2C%20but%20a%20little%20sourly.%20In%202020%2C%20as%20if%20to%20underscore%20Goldman's%20new%20situation%2C%20the%20bank%20was%20forced%20to%20sell%20an%20insurance%20company%20it%20had%20purchased%2C%20Global%20Atlantic%2C%20to%20none%20other%20than%20KKR.%20Because%20under%20the%20crazy%20rules%20of%20our%20current%20regulatory%20system%2C%20an%20unregulated%20private-equity%20firm%20is%20allowed%20to%20own%20an%20insurance%20company%2C%20but%20a%20bank%20is%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20which%20makes%20me%20wonder%3A%20Has%20the%20age%20of%20America's%20last%20great%20investment%20bank%20finally%20come%20to%20an%20end%3F%20Is%20Goldman%20Sachs%20dead%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sense%20that%20Goldman%20was%20no%20longer%20invincible%20didn't%20start%20under%20David%20Solomon's%20watch%2C%20but%20it%20has%20clearly%20accelerated.%20Earlier%20this%20fall%2C%20when%20I%20meet%20with%20him%20in%20a%20conference%20room%20overlooking%20the%20bank's%20trading%20floor%20at%20its%20headquarters%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20Solomon%20is%20defensive.%20There%20has%20always%20been%20dissension%20at%20Goldman%2C%20he%20says%2C%20but%20he%20blames%20the%20press%20for%20serving%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bamplification%20system.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20he%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20most%20threatening%20calls%2C%20like%20those%20in%20a%20slasher%20movie%2C%20are%20coming%20from%20inside%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20definitely%20people%20leaking%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20including%20some%20senior%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20damaging%20the%20firm.%20Clearly.%20Irreparably%3F%20I%20don't%20think%20so%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20dispute%20that%20it's%20damaging%20to%20the%20firm.%20I%20worry%20about%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%20is%20not%20unwilling%20to%20admit%20error.%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20we've%20gotten%20everything%20exactly%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20definitely%20haven't.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20wants%20it%20known%20that%20he%20does%20not%20recognize%20himself%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fintelligencer%2Farticle%2Fdavid-solomon-goldman-sachs-profile.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat's%20been%20written%20about%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He's%20been%20called%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bjerk%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bprick%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bdick.%26quot%3B%20Solomon's%20defenders%20frequently%20use%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Btough%26quot%3B%20to%20explain%20why%20he%20isn't%20well-liked.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20not%20a%20teddy%20bear%2C%26quot%3B%20concedes%20someone%20close%20to%20him.%20Still%2C%20Solomon's%20predecessors%2C%20Blankfein%20and%20Hank%20Paulson%2C%20weren't%20exactly%20known%20for%20being%20soft%20and%20fuzzy.%20What's%20different%20about%20Solomon%20is%20that%20his%20toughness%20is%20unleavened%20by%20Blankfein's%20humor%2C%20or%20by%20Paulson's%20knack%20for%20being%20simultaneously%20ferocious%20and%20oddly%20endearing.%20Solomon%20has%20a%20habit%20of%20beginning%20an%20answer%20by%20questioning%20your%20premise%2C%20or%20by%20quibbling%20with%20something%20you%20said.%20During%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F09%2F07%2Fcnbc-exclusive-cnbc-transcript-goldman-sachs-chairman-ceo-david-solomon-speaks-with-cnbcs-david-faber-on-closing-bell-overtime-today.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20recent%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20California%2C%20when%20the%20CNBC%20anchor%20David%20Faber%20made%20a%20gentle%20joke%20about%