20always%20changing%20%E2%80%94%20Goldman%20seemed%20to%20stay%20one%20step%20ahead%2C%20as%20if%20by%20magic.%20When%20I%20was%20there%2C%20the%20firm%20made%20all%20its%20money%20advising%20on%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%3B%20everything%20else%20was%20a%20sideshow.%20By%20the%202000s%2C%20Goldman%20was%20making%20its%20money%20in%20trading%2C%20and%20banking%20had%20become%20the%20sideshow.%20Once%20the%20firm%20went%20public%2C%20of%20course%2C%20everyone%20knew%20how%20much%20money%20Goldman%20was%20making%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20know%20precisely%20%3Cem%3Ehow%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20was%20getting%20so%20rich.%20That%20was%20part%20of%20the%20mystique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Solomon%2C%20part%20of%20the%20problem%20Goldman%20faces%20is%20people's%20tendency%20to%20view%20its%20previous%20eras%20through%20the%20pretty%20haze%20of%20nostalgia.%20%26quot%3BFantasyland%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20calls%20it.%20In%20our%20conversation%2C%20he's%20eager%20to%20point%20out%20all%20the%20problems%20he%20inherited.%20In%20the%20decade%20before%20he%20became%20CEO%2C%20the%20firm's%20stock%20had%20basically%20flatlined.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBy%202018%2C%20Goldman's%20revenues%20were%20less%20than%20they%20were%20in%202010.%20Even%20more%20alarming%2C%20the%20firm%20was%20losing%20market%20share%20in%20several%20key%20areas%2C%20because%20its%20customers%20were%20tired%20of%20feeling%20as%20if%20Goldman%20were%20out%20to%20get%20them.%20In%20the%20best-known%20episode%2C%20which%20served%20as%20inspiration%20for%20the%20film%20%26quot%3BMargin%20Call%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20dumped%20its%20most%20toxic%20holdings%20just%20before%20the%20financial%20crash%20of%202008%2C%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20some%20of%20its%20customers.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20firm's%20first%20business%20principle%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20clients'%20interests%20always%20come%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20introduced%20in%20the%20days%20of%20the%20legendary%20John%20Whitehead%2C%20became%20something%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20punchline.%20When%20I%20wrote%20about%20the%20firm%20in%202009%2C%20a%20trader%20I%20spoke%20with%20likened%20Goldman%20to%20the%20mob.%20%26quot%3BYou%20do%20business%20with%20them%20because%20you%20have%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20because%20you%20want%20to.%26quot%3B%20A%20friend%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20firm%20recalled%20that%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20his%20mother%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20was%20ashamed%20to%20say%20her%20son%20worked%20at%20Goldman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20financial%20professional%20works%20in%20the%20Goldman%20Sachs%20booth%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20while%20a%20television%20reports%20airs%20about%20the%20company's%20lowered%20stock%20price%20April%2016%2C%202010.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d1c35b788914e55536a23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222226%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20years%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008%2C%20Goldman's%20stock%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20revenues%20%E2%80%94%20took%20a%20beating.%3Cp%3EChris%20Hondros%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%20points%20to%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20financial%20crisis%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eas%20evidence%20that%20the%20firm%20needed%20to%20change.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20went%20up%20to%20someone%20at%20a%20dinner%20party%20and%20said%2C%20'Where%20do%20you%20work%3F'%20the%20answer%20was%3A%20'I%20work%20in%20finance.%20I%20work%20in%20New%20York.'%20People%20were%20embarrassed%20to%20say%20they%20worked%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs.%20Nobody's%20embarrassed%20to%20say%20they%20work%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%20In%20this%20telling%20of%20the%20story%2C%20Solomon%2C%20despite%20his%20flaws%2C%20or%20maybe%20in%20some%20ways%20because%20of%20them%2C%20was%20the%20right%20CEO%20for%20the%20moment.%20He%20was%20willing%20to%20do%20what%20was%20necessary.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20impervious%20to%20what%20people%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20former%20partner%20whose%20views%20of%20Solomon%20are%20mixed.%20%26quot%3BHe%20has%20indomitable%20will.%26quot%3B%20Russell%20Horwitz%2C%20Lloyd%20Blankfein's%20former%20chief%20of%20staff%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-russell-horwitz-david-solomons-new-chief-of-staff-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20made%20headlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20return%20to%20Goldman%20in%20August%2C%20points%20to%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BOur%20Crowd%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20history%20of%20great%20banking%20families%2C%20from%20Rothschild%20to%20Kuhn%20Loeb%20to%20Lehman%2C%20many%20of%20whose%20firms%20have%20disappeared.%20Solomon's%20mindset%2C%20Horowitz%20says%2C%20is%20that%20%26quot%3BGoldman%20doesn't%20have%20a%20preordained%20right%20to%20thrive%2C%20let%20alone%20exist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20CEO%2C%20Solomon%20moved%20quickly%20to%20return%20Goldman%20to%20its%20roots%20as%20a%20client-centered%20firm.%20On%20his%20first%20day%20in%20the%20job%2C%20he%20announced%20an%20initiative%20called%20One%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20in%20which%20employees%20across%20the%20firm%20are%20encouraged%20to%20refer%20business%20to%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20company.%20Satisfaction%20soared%3A%20In%202019%2C%20chief%20operating%20officer%20John%20Waldron%20told%20me%2C%20an%20internal%20survey%20of%20100%20of%20the%20most%20important%20firms%20worldwide%20showed%20that%20only%2044%20ranked%20Goldman%20as%20one%20of%20their%20top%20choices%20when%20they%20needed%20financial%20services.%20Today%20the%20number%20is%2079.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Waldron%20says.%20Goldman%20has%20also%20accomplished%20the%20remarkable%20feat%20of%20remaining%20the%20No.%201%20M%26amp%3BA%20firm%20in%20the%20world%20for%2020%20years%20running.%20%26quot%3BIt%20remains%20the%20crown%20jewel%20of%20Wall%20Street%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dees.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20at%20least%2C%20Goldman%20is%20still%20the%20Goldman%20of%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20even%20after%20the%20IPO%2C%20Goldman%20was%20widely%20perceived%20as%20running%20more%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20its%20partners%20than%20its%20outside%20shareholders.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20it%20was%20not%20really%20acting%20like%20a%20public%20company%20in%20terms%20of%20lack%20of%20transparency%2C%20targets%2C%20investor%20days%2C%20or%20moves%20that%20are%20typical%20of%20a%20Fortune%2050%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20the%20longtime%20bank%20analyst%20Mike%20Mayo.%20Changing%20that%20culture%2C%20he%20says%2C%20was%20bound%20to%20rile%20things%20up.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20truly%20transforming%20a%20company%20that%20for%20two%20decades%20was%20run%20like%20its%20legacy%20self%20and%20you%20now%20want%20it%20to%20run%20like%20a%20Fortune%2050%20company%2C%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20bruised%20egos%20and%20upset%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20cultural%20changes%20at%20Goldman%20since%20the%20IPO%20has%20involved%20the%20way%20partners%20are%20compensated.%20For%20most%20of%20the%20firm's%20history%2C%20partners%20were%20rewarded%20based%20largely%20on%20their%20share%20of%20the%20firm%2C%20rather%20than%20their%20own%20performance.%20That%20meant%20the%20money%20the%20firm%20made%20went%20mostly%20to%20the%20partners%3B%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20IPO%2C%20they%20owned%20about%2060%25%20of%20the%20firm.%20A%20large%20part%20of%20every%20partner's%20net%20worth%20had%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20firm%20until%20their%20retirement.%20It%20was%20socialism%2C%20of%20sorts%2C%20atop%20the%20world's%20most%20capitalistic%20enterprise.%20Everyone%20was%20in%20it%20together%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20there%20was%20no%20place%20else%20on%20Wall%20Street%20you'd%20rather%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223888%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Goldman's%20reputation%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvampire%20squid%26quot%3B%20sparked%20protests%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20also%20contained%20a%20trace%20of%20awe.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e65bcb788914e55540e86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoldman's%20reputation%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvampire%20squid%26quot%3B%20sparked%20protests%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20also%20contained%20a%20trace%20of%20awe.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harrer%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Blankfein%20who%20first%20overhauled%20the%20compensation%20system%20for%20partners%2C%20placing%20a%20far%20greater%20emphasis%20on%20the%20discretionary%20part%20of%20their%20bonuses.%20That%20introduced%20greater%20inequality%20among%20those%20at%20the%20top.%20The%20share%20of%20the%20firm%20that%20partners%20own%20has%20also%20declined%20steadily%20to%20just%20a%20sliver%20today.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20solidarity%20of%20the%20partnership%20is%20no%20longer%20created%20and%20reinforced%20by%20the%20firm's%20financial%20structure.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20total%20amount%20Goldman%20pays%20out%20in%20compensation%20has%20declined%20sharply%20over%20the%20years%2C%20from%20roughly%2050%25%20of%20the%20firm's%20revenues%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20to%20less%20than%2030%25%20today.%20To%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrumbling-at-goldman-sachs-over-david-solomon-bonus-plan-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompensation%20plunged%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20further%20last%20year%2C%20thanks%20to%20losses%20in%20the%20consumer%20business%20and%20a%20slowdown%20in%20the%20markets.%20On%20Wall%20Street%2C%20getting%20paid%20down%20feels%20like%20an%20unbearable%20insult%2C%20even%20if%20the%20absolute%20number%20is%20still%20a%20king's%20ransom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20says%20he%20was%20told%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20that%20broad%20change%20was%20needed.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20board%20who%20gave%20me%20a%20very%2C%20very%20clear%20message%20that%20they%20wanted%20the%20firm%20to%20operate%20more%20like%20a%20public%20company%2C%20with%20a%20mandate%20to%20perform%20for%20shareholders%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20That%20required%20transforming%20the%20culture%20of%20Goldman%20%E2%80%94%20in%20ways%20that%20felt%20to%20some%20partners%20like%20Solomon%20was%20adding%20insult%20on%20top%20of%20the%20injury%20to%20their%20paychecks.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BDavid%20has%20really%20tried%20to%20corporatize%20the%20firm%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one%20partner.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20big%20firm%20now%2C%20he%20feels%2C%20and%20it%20needs%20to%20have%20more%20of%20a%20corporate%20structure%2C%20and%20less%20of%20a%20partnership%20structure.%26quot%3B%20Solomon%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehas%20reorganized%20the%20firm%20not%20once%2C%20but%20three%20times%2C%20in%20part%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20Goldman%20is%20now%20regulated%20as%20a%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20old%20Goldman%20had%20a%20handful%20of%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20fiefdoms%20really%20%E2%80%94%20that%20invested%20the%20firm's%20own%20money%20in%20everything%20from%20real%20estate%20to%20Thai%20baht.%20But%20that%20often%20placed%20Goldman%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20interests%20of%20those%20whose%20assets%20it%20managed.%20When%20the%20firm%20found%20a%20good%20investment%2C%20did%20it%20seize%20the%20opportunity%20for%20itself%2C%20or%20give%20it%20to%20its%20clients%3F%20What's%20more%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20capital%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20began%20to%20require%20Goldman%20to%20hold%20to%20offset%20any%20losses%20in%20its%20deals%20made%20the%20returns%20negligible%2C%20and%20shareholders%20didn't%20like%20the%20unpredictability%20of%20the%20earnings.%20So%20Solomon%20sold%20off%20the%20firm's%20own%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20some%20%2460%20billion%20in%20total%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-private-wealth-management-asset-david-solomon-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efocused%20on%20managing%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20behalf%20of%20outside%20investors%2C%20from%20high-net-worth%20individuals%20to%20pension%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20sparked%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-ceo-david-solomon-profile-why-partners-leaving-4-21%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternal%20disruption%20and%20dissent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BNot%20many%20would%20have%20had%20the%20guts%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Horwitz%2C%20Blankfein's%20former%20chief%20of%20staff.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20senior%20people%2C%20they%20liked%20their%20businesses%2C%20and%20they%20had%20great%20track%20records.%26quot%3B%20Another%20former%20senior%20executive%20recalled%20that%20Blankfein%20recognized%20the%20need%20for%20Solomon's%20move.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20probably%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Blankfein%20told%20the%20executive%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20not%20the%20stuff%20I%20could%20have%20done.%26quot%3B%20Blankfein%2C%20the%20executive%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3Bwas%20too%20culturally%20embedded%20in%20the%20place%26quot%3B%20to%20kill%20the%20fiefdoms%20that%20his%20friends%20had%20spent%20their%20careers%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20plaque%20for%20investment%20banking%20giant%20Goldman%20Sachs%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20in%202009.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d18e9b788914e5553665f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222422%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20old%20Goldman%20was%20dotted%20with%20fiefdoms%20whose%20deals%20sometimes%20placed%20the%20firm%20at%20odds%20with%20its%20own%20clients.%3Cp%3ERichard%20A.%20Brooks%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Image%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20people%20in%20those%20businesses%20viewed%20this%20as%20sacred%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20right%20to%20touch%20it%20and%20change%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Solomon%20says.%20%26quot%3BI've%20looked%20and%20I%20said%2C%20'Could%20I%20have%20handled%20it%20differently%3F'%20I%20don't%20know.%20But%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20whoever%20did%20this%20was%20going%20to%20have%20resistance.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20end%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20the%20right%20result%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20benefit%20we're%20getting%20from%20the%20right%20result%20far%20outweighs%20every%20single%20slight%20or%20every%20single%20anger%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20strategic%20shift%2C%20necessary%20though%20it%20was%2C%20came%20at%20an%20unnecessarily%20steep%20price.%20During%20Solomon's%20tenure%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-partners-who-have-left-under-david-solomon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20200%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20over%2060%20from%20asset%20management%2C%20have%20left%20Goldman%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20significant%20talent%20drain%20at%20a%20time%20when%20it's%20trying%20to%20compete%20with%20private-equity%20firms%20that%20have%20a%20big%20head%20start%20in%20building%20relationships%20with%20large%20institutional%20investors.%20Goldman's%20asset-management%20clients%2C%20a%20former%20partner%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20frustrated%20with%20having%20the%20churn.%26quot%3B%20I've%20heard%20rumblings%20that%20the%20turmoil%20isn't%20over%20%E2%80%94%20and%20these%20days%2C%20rumblings%20seem%20to%20have%20an%20uncomfortable%20way%20of%20becoming%20fact.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Goldman%20boosted%20the%20share%20of%20profits%20that%20investment%20teams%20can%20pocket%20for%20themselves%2C%20more%20closely%20aligning%20their%20compensation%20with%20that%20of%20the%20big%20private-equity%20firms.%20It's%20a%20tacit%20admission%20that%20Goldman%20cannot%20afford%20to%20keep%20losing%20so%20much%20talent%20in%20such%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20its%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20Solomon's%20effort%20to%20build%20the%20consumer%20business%2C%20which%20virtually%20everyone%20I%20spoke%20with%20at%20Goldman%20agrees%20was%20a%20massive%20screwup.%20They%20all%20told%20me%20a%20version%20of%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20that%20Goldman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-marcus-burnout-cloud-tech-hiring-attrition-culture-gs-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20have%20the%20right%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nor%20the%20expertise%2C%20nor%20the%20DNA%2C%20to%20succeed%20as%20a%20retail%20bank.%20The%20basic%20idea%2C%20which%20began%20under%20Blankfein%2C%20wasn't%20wrong%3A%20It%20made%20sense%20to%20diversify%20Goldman's%20funding%20sources%20by%20seeking%20consumer%20deposits%2C%20and%20to%20boost%20the%20firm's%20stock%20by%20creating%20a%20reliable%20stream%20of%20earnings.%20But%20Solomon's%20emphasis%20on%20growing%20the%20business%2C%20and%20fast%2C%20required%20hiring%20way%20more%20people%20to%20meet%20the%20compliance%20requirements%20that%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20places%20on%20retail%20banks.%20From%20the%20end%20of%202018%20through%202022%2C%20Goldman's%20head%20count%20soared%20by%2033%25%2C%20to%2048%2C500%20employees.%20That%20meant%20there%20were%20more%20mouths%20to%20feed%2C%20which%20further%20cut%20into%20the%20compensation%20for%20partners.%20This%20year%2C%20the%20firm%20started%20laying%20people%20off%20%E2%80%94%20over%203%2C000%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20The%20consumer%20business%20%26quot%3Bwas%20set%20up%20in%20a%20way%20that%20made%20it%20obvious%20it%20was%20costing%20us%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20a%20partner.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20wanted%20it%20to%20stop%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Ffinance-and-economics%2F2023%2F08%2F20%2Fgoldman-sachs-has-a-david-solomon-problem%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20criticism%20got%20personal%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20unclear%20is%20whether%20the%20move%20into%20consumer%20banking%20was%20doomed%20from%20the%20start%2C%20or%20whether%20it%20was%20doomed%20because%20of%20the%20way%20Solomon%20went%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20hurry%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-partners-board-david-solomon-revolt-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20enough%20buy-in%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20partners.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20never%20going%20to%20succeed%20during%20one%20CEO's%20tenure%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20long-time%20investor%20says.%20%26quot%3BHe%20made%20it%20too%20big%20too%20fast%20and%20in%20so%20doing%20lost%20the%20chance%20to%20build%20it%20at%20all.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20grow%20these%20businesses%2C%20you%20should%20grow%20them%20one%20step%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20you%20should%20make%20sure%20the%20losses%20aren't%20going%20to%20run%20away%20with%20themselves.%20Because%20if%20it%20goes%20wrong%2C%20then%20you%20damage%20the%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223845%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22DJ%20D-SOL%20performs%20during%20the%20'Safe%20%26amp%3B%20Sound'%20Drive-In%20Concert%20Fundraiser%20on%20July%2025%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d1d9c3cc84b4dfaff89f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222559%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECritics%20sniped%20at%20Solomon%20for%20his%20side%20gig%20as%20a%20DJ%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20retains%20the%20support%20of%20Goldman's%20board.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Mazur%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Safe%20%26amp%3B%20Sound%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPartners%20both%20current%20and%20former%20worry%20that%20Solomon%20has%20already%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20damage%20to%20Goldman.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20strategic%20whiplash%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20for%20the%20organization.%26quot%3B%20Another%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20some%20real%20self-inflicted%20pain%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20which%20we%20didn't%20need%2C%20and%20which%20was%20so%20easily%20avoidable.%26quot%3B%20Insiders%20complain%20that%20Solomon%20not%20only%20failed%20to%20include%20them%20in%20the%20firm's%20new%20direction%2C%20but%20also%20damaged%20the%20culture%20that%20made%20Goldman%20such%20a%20powerhouse%20on%20Wall%20Street.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20firm%20could%20definitely%20be%20more%20partnership-like%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20having%20a%20leadership%20group%20that%20really%20feels%20included%2C%20consulted%2C%20listened%20to%2C%20having%20a%20voice.%20It%20means%20reaching%20out%20more%20broadly%20across%20the%20partnership%20and%20making%20sure%20you've%20got%20proper%20buy-in.%26quot%3B%20Another%20close%20colleague%20says%20Solomon%20has%20so%20far%20failed%20at%20one%20of%20the%20most%20fundamental%20requirements%20of%20leadership%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20he%20did%20a%20good%20job%20bringing%20people%20along%20%E2%80%94%20and%20by%20people%2C%20I%20really%20mean%20the%20partners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20whether%20it's%20fixable%2C%20the%20colleague%20hesitates.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20can%20be%20improved%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BFixed%2C%20I%20don't%20know%2C%20fixed%20is%20a%20harder%20word.%20I%20think%20it%20can%20be%20improved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20truism%20that%20people%20can't%20change.%20But%20sometimes%2C%20when%20there's%20no%20alternative%2C%20they%20do.%20Solomon%20apparently%20tried%20out%20a%20kinder%2C%20gentler%20version%20of%20David%20Solomon%20when%20he%20became%20CEO%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20work.%20%26quot%3BHe%20couldn't%20maintain%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20insider%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20that's%20not%20who%20he%20is.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20relentless%20public%20criticism%20of%20his%20leadership%20has%20been%20enough%20to%20humble%20him.%20%26quot%3BHow%20did%20it%20get%20to%20this%20point%3F%26quot%3B%20another%20insider%20recalls%20Solomon%20asking%20him%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20particularly%20nasty%20media%20maelstrom.%20For%20the%20past%20several%20months%2C%20Solomon%20has%20been%20having%20dinners%20and%20retreats%20with%20small%20groups%20of%20current%20and%20former%20partners%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20to%20listen%20to%20their%20concerns%20and%20criticisms.%20%26quot%3BDavid%20knows%20there's%20a%20problem%20and%20is%20working%20very%20hard%20to%20address%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20top%20retired%20partner%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20the%20criticism%20of%20Solomon%2C%20there's%20a%20key%20constituency%20that%20still%20supports%20him%3A%20Goldman's%20board%20of%20directors.%20The%20disaster%20with%20the%20consumer%20business%20actually%20seems%20to%20have%20enhanced%20his%20standing%20with%20his%20ultimate%20bosses.%20%26quot%3BDavid%20didn't%20start%20it%2C%20but%20his%20name%20was%20on%20it%20and%20he%20knew%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20someone%20familiar%20with%20the%20board%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhats-going-wrong-at-goldman-sachs-marcus-consumer-bank-unit-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecution%20was%20not%20perfect%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20he%20had%20the%20courage%20to%20come%20to%20the%20board%20and%20say%3A%20'You%20know%20what%3F%20This%20isn't%20working.%20We%20have%20to%20do%20something%20different.'%20That's%20what%20leaders%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%2C%20several%20insiders%20tell%20me%2C%20is%20very%2C%20very%20good%20at%20managing%20up.%20Those%20to%20whom%20he%20answers%20apparently%20haven't%20found%20him%20difficult%20in%20the%20way%20those%20who%20answer%20to%20him%20have%3B%20Blankfein%2C%20I'm%20told%2C%20was%20shocked%20to%20hear%20that%20Solomon%20is%20disliked.%20And%20it%20doesn't%20hurt%20that%2C%20last%20year%20aside%2C%20Goldman's%20financial%20performance%20has%20been%20fantastic.%20%26quot%3BJust%20look%20just%20at%20the%20numbers%20since%20David%20has%20been%20the%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20board%20says.%20%26quot%3BOur%20stock%20price%20is%20up%2050%25.%20Our%20returns%20on%20equity%20are%20up.%20We've%20been%20the%20best-%20or%20second-best-performing%20firm%20on%20almost%20every%20metric%20since%20he's%20been%20the%20CEO.%26quot%3B%20Mayo%2C%20the%20longtime%20analyst%2C%20reported%20in%20October%20that%20he'd%20had%20a%20conversation%20with%20Goldman's%20lead%20director%2C%20Adebayo%20Ogunlesi.%20%26quot%3BIn%20that%20meeting%20I%20was%20really%20wondering%2C%20how%20long%20is%20David%20Solomon%20going%20to%20stay%20around%3F%26quot%3B%20Mayo%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20weeks%20or%20months%3F%20But%20the%20answer%20was%20years.%20There's%20no%20question.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20response%20was%2C%20why%20am%20I%20even%20asking%20the%20question%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it's%20the%20market%20that%20will%20determine%20how%20Solomon's%20legacy%20is%20viewed.%20%26quot%3BWinning%20cures%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Mayo%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20the%20capital%20market%20cycle%20turns%20and%20Goldman%20continues%20to%20gain%20share%2C%20then%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20stories%20will%20be%20in%20the%20rearview%20mirror.%26quot%3B%20By%20virtue%20of%20its%20M%26amp%3BA%20business%2C%20Goldman%20is%20still%20very%20much%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20Wall%20Street%20universe.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20number%20one%20in%20advisory%20for%2020%20years%20in%20a%20row%20without%20having%20incredible%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mayo.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20gaining%20the%20most%20market%20share%20of%20anybody%20in%20capital%20markets%20without%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20mojo%20and%20sway%20and%20power.%26quot%3B%20As%20Solomon%20puts%20it%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20the%20middle%20of%20everything%20that%20matters%20in%20the%20world%20financially%2C%20and%20people%20like%20being%20a%20part%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20Solomon's%20argument%20%E2%80%94%20that%20Goldman%20had%20to%20change%20to%20survive%20%E2%80%94%20is%20both%20an%20explanation%20and%20an%20excuse.%20It's%20true.%20But%20if%20survival%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20firm's%20partnership%2C%20then%20Goldman%20is%20no%20longer%20Goldman.%20Throughout%20the%20firm's%20many%20changes%20over%20the%20years%2C%20it's%20the%20power%20and%20stability%20of%20its%20partnership%2C%20ultimately%2C%20that%20made%20Goldman%20special.%20The%20real%20trick%20of%20leadership%20is%20not%20choosing%20between%20a%20partnership%20or%20a%20corporation%2C%20but%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20profit%20from%20the%20benefits%20of%20both.%20If%20Goldman%20transforms%20itself%20into%20just%20another%20financial-services%20firm%2C%20why%20would%20anyone%20choose%20to%20work%20there%20instead%20of%20at%20Blackstone%20or%20Citadel%2C%20or%20even%20JPMorgan%20or%20Bank%20of%20America%3F%20And%20if%20the%20firm%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20most%20desirable%20place%20to%20work%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20then%20Goldman%20Sachs%20as%20we've%20known%20it%20is%20truly%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224038%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Traders%20at%20Computer%20Terminals%20in%20Goldman%20Sachs%20Office%20in%201999.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d1adeb788914e555368fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222726%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Goldman%20Sachs%20that%20existed%20prior%20to%20its%20IPO%20is%20dead.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20swashbuckling%20traders%20of%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20concedes%20the%20firm's%20head%20of%20global%20banking%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20do%20think%20there's%20some%20romance%20lost%20there.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EJames%20Leynse%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20internal%20issue%20is%20the%20external%20one%3A%20the%20meteoric%20rise%20of%20private%20equity%20and%20hedge%20funds%2C%20which%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-alumni-being-hired-by-top-hedge-funds-2023-3%3Fop%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esiphoning%20talent%3C%2Fa%3E%20away%20from%20Goldman.%20Solomon%20points%20out%20that%20talented%20people%20have%20always%20left%20Goldman%2C%20and%20by%20some%20measures%2C%20now%20is%20no%20different.%20But%20it's%20clearly%20a%20major%20worry.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20big%2C%20big%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20John%20Waldron%2C%20the%20firm's%20chief%20operating%20officer.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20wrestling%20with%20how%20to%20navigate%20it.%20Because%2C%20with%20humility%2C%20we%20believe%20we%20have%20the%20best%20talent%20in%20our%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20can't%20not%20have%20the%20best%20talent%20in%20our%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20confess%20I'm%20guilty%20of%20a%20certain%20nostalgia%20when%20I%20think%20about%20Goldman.%20It's%20hard%2C%20despite%20the%20firm's%20many%20flaws%20and%20misdeeds%2C%20not%20to%20look%20back%20with%20a%20degree%20of%20respect%20for%20the%20place%20that%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%20power%2C%20and%20the%20vagaries%2C%20of%20high%20finance.%20But%20I'm%20also%20guilty%20of%20a%20very%20dangerous%2C%20and%20very%20common%2C%20misperception%3A%20that%20the%20Wall%20Street%20of%20tomorrow%20will%20remain%20what%20it%20is%20today.%20It%20will%20not.%20The%20very%20first%20story%20I%20worked%20on%20when%20I%20started%20off%20in%20journalism%20in%201995%20was%20about%20Lehman's%20comeback%20as%20a%20stand-alone%20firm%2C%20after%20its%20spinoff%20from%20American%20Express.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20no%20one%20could%20have%20guessed%20that%20in%20little%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20Lehman%20and%20so%20many%20other%20financial%20giants%20would%20vanish%20into%20the%20ether.%20Today%2C%20as%20we%20approach%20the%2025th%20anniversary%20of%20Goldman's%20IPO%2C%20we're%20also%20passing%20the%20quarter-century%20mark%20since%20the%20hedge%20fund%20Long-Term%20Capital%20Management%20imploded%20over%20its%20%244.6%20billion%20in%20high-risk%20investments.%20Yes%2C%20at%20the%20moment%20it's%20the%20big%2C%20market-moving%20hedge%20funds%20and%20private-equity%20firms%2C%20which%20now%20control%20vast%20swaths%20of%20American%20business%2C%20that%20are%20allowed%20to%20operate%20beyond%20the%20reach%20of%20regulators.%20But%20that%20financial%20ecosystem%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20ones%20that%20enabled%20Lehman%20and%20so%20many%20other%20failed%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20will%20one%20day%20crash%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20its%20own%20excesses.%20And%20when%20it%20does%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20will%20still%20be%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENor%20is%20reinvention%20anything%20new%20for%20Goldman.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20firm%20almost%20collapsed%20in%20the%20mid-1970s%20when%20Penn%20Central%2C%20for%20which%20Goldman%20had%20sold%20commercial%20paper%2C%20went%20bankrupt.%20In%201994%2C%20huge%20trading%20losses%20resulted%20in%20a%20mass%20exodus%20of%20partners%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20the%20risk%20that%20their%20entire%20net%20worth%20would%20vanish%20if%20the%20firm%20failed.%20And%20there%20was%20the%20fight%20over%20the%20IPO%2C%20which%20helped%20lead%20to%20Corzine's%20ouster.%20The%20firm%20has%20always%20managed%20to%20emerge%20from%20its%20internal%20battles%2C%20and%20its%20external%20challenges%2C%20as%20powerful%20as%20ever.%20Maybe%20it's%20core%20DNA%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20is%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20swashbuckling%20traders%20of%20old%2C%20and%20I%20do%20think%20there's%20some%20lost%20romance%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dees%2C%20my%20fellow%20analyst%20who%20now%20heads%20global%20banking%20and%20markets%20for%20Goldman.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20look%20and%20say%2C%20'Ah%2C%20that%20period%20of%20yesteryear%20where%20someone%20could%20put%20a%20trade%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20distressed%20credits%20in%20Thailand%20and%20make%20a%20billion%20dollars%20and%20beat%20his%20chest'%20%E2%80%94%20I%20get%20it.%20But%20that's%20not%20realistic.%20They're%20nostalgic%20for%20a%20thing%20that%20can't%20exist%20today%20at%20any%20bank%2C%20under%20the%20current%20regulatory%20system.%20This%20place%20is%20still%20about%20excellence.%20It's%20just%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20in%20a%20different%20format.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20is%20dead.%20Long%20live%20Goldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fbethany-mc-lean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBethany%20McLean%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20special%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frip-goldman-sachs-wall-street-investment-bank-dead-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699958702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655234c436d588dc55cf3cbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frip-goldman-sachs-wall-street-investment-bank-dead-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20I%20started%20out%20at%20Goldman%2C%20it%20was%20the%20most%20feared%20firm%20on%20Wall%20Street.%20Those%20days%20are%20gone%20for%20good.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Bethany%20McLean)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frip-goldman-sachs-wall-street-investment-bank-dead-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%2