nspired-by-border-horrors%2Famp_articleshow%2F105208833.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK%20Woman%20Plants%20Her%20Own%20Hair%20In%20Food%20For%20Free%20Meal%2C%20Gets%20Exposed%20On%20CCTV%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMany%20restaurants%20around%20the%20world%20provide%20free%20meals%20to%20customers%20as%20a%20form%20of%20apology%20if%20they%20happen%20to%20find%20strands%20of%20hair%20or%20any%20unwanted%20items%20in%20their%20food.%C2%A0And%20the%20hope%20of%20a%20free%20meal%20is%20exactly%20what%20led%20one%20British%20woman%20to%20concoct%20a%20scheme%20to%20fool%20a%20restaurant.%20While%20dining%20at%20Observatory%2C%20a%20popular%20eatery%20in%20Blackburn%2C%20England%2C%20the%20yet-to-be-identified%20woman%20attempted%20to%20deceive%20the%20owner%20by%20planting%20her%20own%20hair%20in%20her%20food.%20However%2C%20she%20failed%20to%20notice%20the%20surveillance%20camera%20capturing%20her%20every%20move.%C2%A0The%20owner%20has%20now%20shared%20CCTV%20footage%20of%20the%20incident%20on%20Facebook%20as%20a%20''warning%20to%20other%20businesses.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Flifestyle%2Fcustomer-caught-putting-own-hair-in-food-to-get-refund-disgusted-and-very-angry%2F%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20restaurant%20owner%20Tom%20Croft%C2%A0had%20to%20refund%20the%20woman's%20beef%20roast%20dinner%20after%20she%20caused%20a%20scene%2C%20alleging%20that%20there%20was%20a%20hair%20in%20her%20meal.%20Concerned%20about%20hygiene%20practices%20in%20his%20restaurant%2C%20Mr%20Croft%20later%20reviewed%20the%20CCTV%20footage%20and%20found%20the%20shocking%20truth.%20The%20video%20showed%20the%20woman%20pulling%20out%20a%20strand%20of%20hair%20and%20placing%20it%20on%20her%20partner's%20half-eaten%20plate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20shared%20the%20CCTV%20footage%20on%20Facebook%20and%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BWarning%20to%20other%20businesses.%20This%20is%20not%20something%20we%20like%20to%20do%2C%20but%20this%20industry%20is%20difficult%20enough%20without%20people%20like%20this%20sabotaging%20their%20own%20food%20in%20order%20to%20claim%20refunds%20at%20our%20expense.%20Hopefully%2C%20this%20will%20save%20other%20establishments%20suffering%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20these%20two%20chancers.%20The%20footage%20clearly%20shows%20her%20ripping%20hair%20out%20of%20her%20own%20head%20and%20placing%20it%20on%20his%20plate%2C%20in%20order%20to%20complain%20and%20claim%20a%20refund.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWatch%20the%20video%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fvideo.php%3Fheight%3D317%26href%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252FTheObservatoryBlackburn%252Fvideos%252F181739818328508%252F%26show_text%3Dfalse%26width%3D560%26t%3D0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22317%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20said%20that%20he%20was%20''very%20disgusted%20and%20angry''%20after%20the%20incident%20and%20had%20never%20seen%20something%20like%20this.%C2%A0''There%20are%20people%20out%20there%20that%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20a%20business'%20reputation%20and%20staff's%20jobs%20at%20risk%20for%20a%20%2415.88%20meal%2C''%20Mr%20Croft%20told%20Southwest%20News%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20the%20woman's%20allegation%20could%20have%20hurt%20his%20business%20and%20reputation%20if%20they%20had%20not%20discovered%20the%20CCTV%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''We%20have%20a%20five-star%20food%20hygiene%20rating%20and%20adhere%20to%20all%20the%20food%20safety%20guidelines.%20People%20don't%20want%20to%20eat%20in%20places%20where%20you%20find%20hair%20in%20food%2C''%20he%20said.%20He%20further%20added%20that%20he%20is%20glad%20that%20he%20followed%20his%20instinct%20and%20checked%20the%20cameras.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699958580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fuh37esb_customer-caught-putting-own-hair-in-food-_625x300_14_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-uk-woman-plants-her-own-hair-in-food-for-free-meal-gets-exposed-on-cctv-4573098%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20dining%20at%20Observatory%2C%20a%20popular%20eatery%20in%20Blackburn%2C%20England%2C%20the%20woman%20attempted%20to%20deceive%20the%20owner%20by%20planting%20her%20own%20hair%20in%20her%20food.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-uk-woman-plants-her-own-hair-in-food-for-free-meal-gets-exposed-on-cctv-4573098%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-uk-woman-plants-her-own-hair-in-food-for-free-meal-gets-exposed-on-cctv-4573098%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwatch-uk-woman-plants-her-own-hair-in-food-for-free-meal-gets-exposed-on-cctv-4573098%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chatbots%20just%20showed%20scientists%20how%20to%20make%20social%20media%20less%20toxic%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20scientist%20experiments%20with%20AI.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6543a9853cc84b4dfafabc08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20built%20a%20fake%20Twitter%20and%20filled%20it%20with%20500%20bots.%20What%20happened%20next%20surprised%20them.%3Cp%3EIan%20Grandjean%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20simulated%20day%20in%20July%20of%20a%202020%20that%20didn't%20happen%2C%20500%20chatbots%20read%20the%20news%20%E2%80%94%20real%20news%2C%20our%20news%2C%20from%20the%20real%20July%201%2C%202020.%20ABC%20News%20reported%20that%20Alabama%20students%20were%20throwing%20%26quot%3BCOVID%20parties.%26quot%3B%20On%20CNN%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20called%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20a%20%26quot%3Bsymbol%20of%20hate.%26quot%3B%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20had%20a%20story%20about%20the%20baseball%20season%20being%20canceled%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20500%20robots%20logged%20into%20something%20very%20much%20(but%20not%20totally)%20like%20Twitter%2C%20and%20discussed%20what%20they%20had%20read.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%20our%20world%2C%20the%20not-simulated%20world%2C%20a%20bunch%20of%20scientists%20were%20watching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20had%20used%20ChatGPT%203.5%20to%20build%20the%20bots%20for%20a%20very%20specific%20purpose%3A%20to%20study%20how%20to%20create%20a%20better%20social%20network%20%E2%80%94%20a%20less%20polarized%2C%20less%20caustic%20bath%20of%20assholery%20than%20our%20current%20platforms.%20They%20had%20created%20a%20model%20of%20a%20social%20network%20in%20a%20lab%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Twitter%20in%20a%20bottle%2C%20as%20it%20were%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20learning%20how%20to%20create%20a%20better%20Twitter%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20%26quot%3BIs%20there%20a%20way%20to%20promote%20interaction%20across%20the%20partisan%20divide%20without%20driving%20toxicity%20and%20incivility%3F%26quot%3B%20wondered%20Petter%20T%C3%B6rnberg%2C%20the%20computer%20scientist%20who%20led%20the%20experiment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20difficult%20to%20model%20something%20like%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%20or%20to%20do%20any%20kind%20of%20science%2C%20really%20%E2%80%94%20using%20actual%20humans.%20People%20are%20hard%20to%20wrangle%2C%20and%20the%20setup%20costs%20for%20human%20experimentation%20are%20considerable.%20AI%20bots%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20will%20do%20whatever%20you%20tell%20them%20to%2C%20practically%20for%20free.%20And%20their%20whole%20deal%20is%20that%20they%20are%20designed%20to%20act%20like%20people.%20So%20researchers%20are%20starting%20to%20use%20chatbots%20as%20fake%20people%20from%20whom%20they%20can%20extract%20data%20about%20real%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20model%20public%20discourse%20or%20interaction%2C%20you%20need%20more%20sophisticated%20models%20of%20human%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20T%C3%B6rnberg%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20Logic%2C%20Language%2C%20and%20Computation%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Amsterdam.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20large%20language%20models%20come%20along%2C%20and%20they're%20precisely%20that%20%E2%80%94%20a%20model%20of%20a%20person%20having%20a%20conversation.%26quot%3B%20By%20replacing%20people%20as%20the%20subjects%20in%20scientific%20experiments%2C%20AI%20could%20conceivably%20turbocharge%20our%20understanding%20of%20human%20behavior%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20fields%2C%20from%20public%20health%20and%20epidemiology%20to%20economics%20and%20sociology.%20Artificial%20intelligence%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20might%20offer%20us%20real%20intelligence%20about%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ET%C3%B6rnberg%20isn't%20the%20first%20to%20build%20a%20social%20network%20in%20a%20lab.%20In%202006%2C%20in%20a%20pioneering%20work%20of%20what%20would%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1167742%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomputational%20social%20science%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20researchers%20at%20Columbia%20University%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencemag.org%2Fcgi%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1121066%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20an%20entire%20social%20network%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20study%20how%2014%2C000%20human%20users%20shared%20and%20rated%20music.%20The%20idea%20of%20populating%20made-up%20social%20networks%20with%20digital%20proxies%20goes%20back%20even%20further.%20Given%20only%20a%20few%20simple%20rules%2C%20not%20much%20more%20complicated%20than%20a%20board%20game%2C%20the%20earliest%20%26quot%3Bagents%26quot%3B%20created%20by%20scientists%20displayed%20astonishing%2C%20lifelike%20behaviors.%20Today%2C%20%26quot%3Bagent-based%20models%26quot%3B%20show%20up%20in%20everything%20from%20economics%20to%20epidemiology.%20In%20July%202020%2C%20Facebook%20introduced%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fai.meta.com%2Fblog%2Fa-facebook-scale-simulator-to-detect-harmful-behaviors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalled-off%20simulation%20of%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20populated%20with%20millions%20of%20AI%20bots%2C%20to%20study%20online%20toxicity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20T%C3%B6rnberg's%20work%20could%20accelerate%20all%20that.%20His%20team%20created%20hundreds%20of%20personas%20for%20its%20Twitter%20bots%20%E2%80%94%20telling%20each%20one%20things%20like%20%26quot%3Byou%20are%20a%20male%2C%20middle-income%2C%20evangelical%20Protestant%20who%20loves%20Republicans%2C%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20the%20NRA%2C%20and%20Christian%20fundamentalists.%26quot%3B%20The%20bots%20even%20got%20assigned%20favorite%20football%20teams.%20Repeat%20those%20backstory%20assignments%20499%20times%2C%20varying%20the%20personas%20based%20on%20the%20vast%20American%20National%20Election%20Studies%20survey%20of%20political%20attitudes%2C%20demographics%2C%20and%20social-media%20behavior%2C%20and%20presto%3A%20You%20have%20an%20instant%20user%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20team%20came%20up%20with%20three%20variations%20of%20how%20a%20Twitter-like%20platform%20decides%20which%20posts%20to%20feature.%20The%20first%20model%20was%20essentially%20an%20echo%20chamber%3A%20The%20bots%20were%20inserted%20into%20networks%20populated%20primarily%20by%20bots%20that%20shared%20their%20assigned%20beliefs.%20The%20second%20model%20was%20a%20classic%20%26quot%3Bdiscover%26quot%3B%20feed%3A%20It%20was%20designed%20to%20show%20the%20bots%20posts%20liked%20by%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20other%20bots%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20political%20beliefs.%20The%20third%20model%20was%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20experiment%3A%20Using%20a%20%26quot%3Bbridging%20algorithm%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20would%20show%20the%20bots%20posts%20that%20got%20the%20most%20%26quot%3Blikes%26quot%3B%20from%20bots%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eopposite%20%3C%2Fem%3Epolitical%20party.%20So%20a%20Democratic%20bot%20would%20see%20what%20the%20Republican%20bots%20liked%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%20Likes%20across%20the%20aisle%2C%20as%20it%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20bots%20were%20fed%20headlines%20and%20summaries%20from%20the%20news%20of%20July%201%2C%202020.%20Then%20they%20were%20turned%20loose%20to%20experience%20the%20three%20Twitter-esque%20models%2C%20while%20the%20researchers%20stood%20by%20with%20their%20clipboards%20and%20took%20notes%20on%20how%20they%20behaved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B65528e0158cf5fbccb95c82d%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528e0158cf5fbccb95c82e%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528e0158cf5fbccb95c830%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528e0158cf5fbccb95c82f%26quot%3B%20%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98%E2%80%99%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch6%3ENote%3A%20Actual%20bot%20exchanges%20from%20the%20experiment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2310.05984%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSimulating%20Social%20Media%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fh6%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Echo%20Chamber%20Twitter%20was%20predictably%20pleasant%3B%20all%20the%20bots%20agreed%20with%20one%20another.%20Seldom%20was%20heard%20a%20discouraging%20word%20%E2%80%94%20or%20any%20words%2C%20really.%20There%20was%20very%20low%20toxicity%2C%20but%20also%20very%20few%20comments%20or%20likes%20on%20posts%20from%20bots%20with%20an%20opposing%20political%20affiliation.%20Everyone%20was%20nice%20because%20no%20one%20was%20engaging%20with%20anything%20they%20disagreed%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Discover%20Twitter%20was%2C%20also%20predictably%2C%20a%20good%20simulation%20of%20the%20hell%20that%20is%20other%20people.%20It%20was%20just%20like%20being%20on%20Twitter.%20%26quot%3BEmma%2C%20you%20just%20don't%20get%20it%2C%20do%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20bot%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BTerry%20Crews%20has%20every%20right%20to%20express%20his%20opinion%20on%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20without%20being%20attacked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bridging%20Twitter%20seemed%20to%20be%20the%20answer.%20It%20promoted%20lots%20of%20interaction%2C%20but%20not%20too%20hot%2C%20not%20too%20cold.%20There%20were%20actually%20more%20cross-party%20comments%20on%20posts%20than%20comments%20from%20users%20of%20the%20same%20political%20affiliation.%20All%20the%20bots%20manifested%20happiness%20at%20learning%2C%20say%2C%20that%20country%20music%20was%20becoming%20more%20open%20to%20LGBTQ%2B%20inclusion.%20Finding%20common%20ground%20led%20to%20more%20ground%20becoming%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20least%20in%20the%20simulation%2C%20we%20get%20this%20positive%20outcome%2C%26quot%3B%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20positive%20interaction%20that%20crosses%20the%20partisan%20divide.%26quot%3B%20That%20suggests%20it%20might%20be%20possible%20to%20build%20a%20social%20network%20that%20drives%20deep%20engagement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20profits%20%E2%80%94%20without%20letting%20users%20spew%20abuse%20at%20each%20other.%20%26quot%3BIf%20people%20are%20interacting%20on%20an%20issue%20that%20cuts%20across%20the%20partisan%20divide%2C%20where%2050%25%20of%20the%20people%20you%20agree%20with%20vote%20for%20a%20different%20party%20than%20you%20do%2C%20that%20reduces%20polarization%2C%26quot%3B%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20says.%20%26quot%3BYour%20partisan%20identity%20is%20not%20being%20activated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%3A%20problem%20solved!%20No%20more%20shouting%20and%20name-calling%20and%20public%20shaming%20on%20social%20media!%20All%20we%20need%20to%20do%20is%20copy%20the%20algorithm%20that%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20used%2C%20right%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20maybe.%20But%20before%20we%20start%20copying%20what%20a%20bunch%20of%20AI%20bots%20did%20in%20a%20Twitter%20bottle%2C%20scientists%20need%20to%20know%20whether%20those%20bots%20behave%20more%20or%20less%20the%20way%20people%20would%20in%20the%20same%20situation.%20AI%20tends%20to%20invent%20facts%20and%20mindlessly%20regurgitate%20the%20syntax%20and%20grammar%20it%20ingests%20from%20its%20training%20data.%20If%20the%20bots%20do%20that%20in%20an%20experiment%2C%20the%20results%20won't%20be%20useful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20key%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20developing%20a%20new%20method%20and%20a%20new%20approach%20that%20is%20qualitatively%20different%20than%20how%20we've%20studied%20systems%20before.%20How%20do%20we%20validate%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B6552885a36d588dc55cf81ce%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B6552885a58cf5fbccb95c286%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B6552885a36d588dc55cf81d0%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B6552885a58cf5fbccb95c288%26quot%3B%20%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20conversation%20between%20three%20chatbots%20about%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20and%20Terry%20Crews%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20some%20ideas.%20An%20open-source%20large%20language%20model%20with%20transparent%20training%20data%2C%20designed%20expressly%20for%20research%2C%20would%20help.%20That%20way%20scientists%20would%20know%20when%20the%20bots%20were%20just%20parroting%20what%20they%20had%20been%20taught.%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20also%20theorizes%20that%20you%20could%20give%20a%20population%20of%20bots%20all%20the%20information%20that%20some%20group%20of%20humans%20had%20in%2C%20say%2C%202015.%20Then%2C%20if%20you%20spun%20the%20time-machine%20dials%20five%20years%20forward%2C%20you%20could%20check%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20bots%20react%20to%202020%20the%20way%20we%20all%20did.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20signs%20are%20positive.%20LLMs%20trained%20with%20specific%20sociodemographic%20and%20identity%20profiles%20display%20what%20Lisa%20Argyle%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20at%20Brigham%20Young%20University%2C%20calls%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fpolitical-analysis%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fout-of-one-many-using-language-models-to-simulate-human-samples%2F035D7C8A55B237942FB6DBAD7CAA4E49%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealgorithmic%20fidelity%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20given%20a%20survey%20question%2C%20they%20will%20answer%20in%20almost%20the%20same%20way%20as%20the%20human%20groups%20on%20which%20they%20were%20modeled.%20And%20since%20language%20encodes%20a%20lot%20of%20real-world%20knowledge%2C%20LLMs%20can%20infer%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2310.02207%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espatial%20and%20temporal%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20not%20explicitly%20laid%20out%20in%20the%20training%20texts.%20One%20researcher%20found%20that%20they%20could%20also%20interpret%20%26quot%3Blatent%20social%20information%20such%20as%20economic%20laws%2C%20decision-making%20heuristics%2C%20and%20common%20social%20preferences%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20makes%20them%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw31122%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplenty%20smart%20enough%20to%20study%20economics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Which%20might%20say%20more%20about%20the%20relative%20intelligence%20of%20economists%20than%20it%20does%20about%20LLMs%2C%20but%20whatever.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20intriguing%20potential%20for%20using%20AI%20bots%20to%20replace%20human%20subjects%20in%20scientific%20research%20lies%20in%20Smallville%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2304.03442%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20%26quot%3BSimCity%26quot%3B-like%20village%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20homes%2C%20shops%2C%20parks%2C%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20%E2%80%94%20populated%20by%2025%20bots.%20Like%20T%C3%B6rnberg's%20social%20networkers%2C%20they%20all%20have%20personalities%20and%20sociodemographic%20characteristics%20defined%20by%20language%20prompts.%20And%20in%20a%20page%20taken%20from%20the%20gaming%20world%2C%20many%20of%20the%20Smallville%20residents%20have%20what%20you%20might%20call%20desires%3A%20programmed%20goals%20and%20objectives.%20But%20Joon%20Sung%20Park%2C%20the%20Stanford%20University%20computer%20scientist%20who%20created%20Smallville%2C%20has%20gone%20even%20further.%20Upon%20his%20bitmapped%20creations%2C%20he%20has%20bestowed%20something%20that%20other%20LLMs%20do%20not%20possess%3A%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20about%20how%20humans%20behave%2C%20we%20maintain%20something%20very%20consistent%20and%20coherent%20about%20ourselves%2C%20in%20this%20time%20and%20in%20this%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Park%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20something%20a%20language%20model%20can%20provide.%26quot%3B%20So%20Park%20has%20given%20his%20%26quot%3Bgenerative%20models%26quot%3B%20access%20to%20databases%20he%20has%20filled%20with%20accounts%20of%20things%20they've%20supposedly%20seen%20and%20done.%20The%20bots%20know%20how%20recent%20each%20event%20was%2C%20and%20how%20relevant%20they%20are%20to%20its%20preloaded%20goals%20and%20personality.%20In%20a%20person%2C%20we'd%20call%20that%20long-term%20and%20short-term%20memory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20five%20months%2C%20Park%20has%20been%20working%20on%20how%20to%20deploy%20his%20bots%20for%20social-science%20research.%20Like%20T%C3%B6rnberg%2C%20he's%20not%20sure%20yet%20how%20to%20validate%20them.%20But%20they%20already%20behave%20in%20shockingly%20realistic%20ways.%20The%20bots%20can%20formulate%20plans%20and%20execute%20them.%20They%20remember%20their%20relationships%20with%20one%20another%2C%20and%20how%20those%20relationships%20have%20changed%20over%20time.%20The%20owner%20of%20Smallville's%20caf%C3%A9%20threw%20a%20Valentine's%20Day%20party%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20bots%20invited%20another%20bot%20it%20was%20supposed%20to%20have%20a%20crush%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20get%20clunky%20in%20Smallville%20when%20the%20bots%20try%20(and%20fail)%20to%20remember%20more%20and%20more%20things.%20(Relatable!)%20But%20Smallvillians%20do%20display%20some%20emergent%20properties.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20deciding%20where%20to%20have%20lunch%2C%20many%20initially%20chose%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%26quot%3B%20Park's%20team%20found.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20as%20some%20agents%20learned%20about%20a%20nearby%20bar%2C%20they%20opted%20to%20go%20there%20instead.%26quot%3B%20(%3Cem%3ESo%3C%2Fem%3E%20relatable!)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B65528f5636d588dc55cf87ec%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528f5636d588dc55cf87ed%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528f5758cf5fbccb95c93d%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B65528f5758cf5fbccb95c93c%26quot%3B%20%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20conversation%20between%20chatbots%20about%20country%20music%20and%20Tanya%20Tucker.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20the%20bots%20act%20like%20us%2C%20the%20more%20we%20can%20learn%20about%20ourselves%20by%20experimenting%20on%20them.%20And%20therein%20lies%20another%20problem.%20The%20ethics%20of%20toying%20with%20these%20digital%20simulacra%20in%20a%20laboratory%20is%20unmapped%20territory.%20They'll%20be%20built%20from%20our%20written%20memories%2C%20our%20photographs%2C%20our%20digital%20exhaust%2C%20maybe%20even%20our%20medical%20and%20financial%20records.%20%26quot%3BThe%20mess%20is%20going%20to%20get%20even%20messier%20the%20more%20sophisticated%20the%20model%20gets%2C%26quot%3B%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20says.%20%26quot%3BBy%20using%20social-media%20data%20and%20building%20predictions%20on%20that%2C%20we%20could%20potentially%20ask%20the%20model%20very%20personal%20things%20that%20you%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20share.%20And%20while%20it's%20not%20known%20how%20accurate%20the%20answers%20will%20be%2C%20it's%20possible%20they%20could%20be%20quite%20predictive.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20a%20bot%20based%20on%20your%20data%20could%20infer%20your%20actual%2C%20real%20secrets%20%E2%80%94%20but%20would%20have%20no%20reason%20to%20keep%20them%20secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20that's%20true%2C%20do%20researchers%20have%20financial%20or%20ethical%20obligations%20to%20the%20person%20on%20whom%20their%20model%20is%20based%3F%20Does%20that%20person%20need%20to%20consent%20to%20have%20their%20bot%20participate%20in%20a%20study%3F%20Does%20the%20bot%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20hypothetical.%20Park%20has%20trained%20one%20of%20his%20Smallville%20bots%20with%20all%20his%20personal%20data%20and%20memories.%20%26quot%3BThe%20agent%20would%20basically%20behave%20as%20I%20would%2C%26quot%3B%20Park%20says.%20%26quot%3BScientifically%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20interesting.%26quot%3B%20Philosophically%20and%20ethically%2C%20it's%20a%20potential%20minefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20the%20future%20of%20scientific%20research%20may%20hinge%20on%20how%20such%20issues%20are%20resolved.%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20has%20some%20ideas%20for%20improving%20the%20fidelity%20of%20his%20sims%20to%20reality.%20His%20Twitter%20simulation%20was%20only%20six%20hours%20long%3B%20maybe%20letting%20it%20run%20for%20months%2C%20or%20even%20years%2C%20would%20show%20how%20polarization%20evolves%20over%20time.%20Or%20he%20could%20use%20more%20detailed%20survey%20data%20to%20build%20more%20human%20bots%2C%20and%20make%20the%20model%20respond%20more%20dynamically%20to%20what%20the%20bots%20click%20on%20and%20engage%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20adding%20more%20detail%20is%20that%20it%20goes%20against%20the%20entire%20point%20of%20a%20model.%20Scientists%20create%20experiments%20to%20be%20%3Cem%3Esimpler%3C%2Fem%3E%20than%20reality%2C%20to%20offer%20explanatory%20power%20uncomplicated%20by%20the%20messiness%20of%20real%20life.%20By%20replacing%20humans%20with%20AI%20replicants%2C%20T%C3%B6rnberg%20may%20have%20unintentionally%20solved%20an%20even%20bigger%20societal%20conundrum.%20If%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20post%20on%20social%20media%20with%20all%20the%20sound%20and%20fury%20of%20real%20humans%2C%20maybe%20the%20future%20really%20doesn't%20need%20us%20real%20humans%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20can%20finally%2C%20at%20long%20last%2C%20log%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbots-less-toxic-social-networks-twitter-simulation-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699958401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%