span%3EFor%20Jews%2C%20it%20is%20the%20Mount%20of%20Anointment%2C%20as%20the%20pressed%20oil%20from%20its%20olives%20was%20used%20to%20anoint%20Israelite%20kings%20in%20the%20ancient%20past.%20A%20large%20part%20of%20the%20mount%20is%20covered%20with%20what%20is%20today%20known%20as%20the%20Jewish%20cemetery%2C%20and%20most%20of%20the%20Jews%20want%20to%20be%20buried%20here%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20several%20scriptural%20prophecies%20their%20faith%20revolves%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20422px)%2085vw%2C%20422px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14151643%2Funnamed-2-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22422%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14151643%2Funnamed-2-1.jpg%20810w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14151643%2Funnamed-2-1-237x300.jpg%20237w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684692%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EConvent%20of%20St.%20Catherine%2C%20by%20David%20Roberts%2C%201839%2C%20Library%20of%20Congress%20Archives%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOlives%20are%20also%20considered%20a%20blessed%20fruit%20in%20Islam.%20Prophet%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20very%20fond%20of%20olives%20and%20in%20fact%20encouraged%20people%20to%20grow%2C%20use%20and%20cherish%20the%20tree%E2%80%99s%20fruits%2C%20especially%20applauding%20the%20oil%E2%80%99s%20medicinal%20values.%20In%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esurah-an-noor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20lamp%20that%20guides%20humankind%20towards%20light%20in%20darkness%2C%20is%20lit%20by%20the%20oil%20of%20the%20blessed%20tree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.internationaloliveoil.org%2Folive-world%2Folive-tree%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20spread%20of%20olive%20trees%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20around%20the%20Mediterranean%20and%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20occurred%20from%20Asia%20Minor%2C%20Levant%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Palestine%20(trees%20like%20Noah%E2%80%99s%20sisters%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20Al-Badawi%20in%20Palestine%20are%20estimated%20to%20be%206000%20to%202000%20years%20old).%20Mount%20Sinai%20in%20Egypt%2C%20sacred%20to%20all%20three%20Abrahamic%20religions%2C%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20olive%20tree%20scriptural%20references.%20The%20sixth%20century%20St.%20Catherine%E2%80%99s%20monastery%20at%20the%20northern%20foot%20of%20Sinai%20has%20olive%20trees%20growing%20in%20its%20courtyard.%20Another%20verse%20in%20Quran%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esurah-at-tin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20speaks%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ezaytoun%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Etur-Sinai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20olives%20at%20mount%20Sinai%2C%20%E2%80%9Cby%20the%20fig%20and%20the%20olives%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dove%20with%20an%20olive%20branch%20in%20Genesis%2C%20has%20become%20a%20symbol%20of%20reconciliation%20between%20the%20human%20and%20the%20divine.%20In%20the%20old-testament%2C%20Noah%2C%20now%20having%20taken%20refuge%20in%20the%20ark%20for%20seven%20months%2C%20sends%20the%20birds%2C%20a%20raven%20and%20a%20dove%20to%20go%20see%20if%20the%20waters%20of%20the%20flood%20had%20subsided.%20The%20raven%20never%20returned%20and%20kept%20flying%20until%20dry%20land%20emerged%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20floods.%20The%20dove%20does%20return%20without%20finding%20dry%20land%20anywhere.%20After%20seven%20days%2C%20he%20sends%20the%20dove%20out%20again%2C%20only%20this%20time%20she%20returns%20with%20an%20olive-twig%20in%20her%20beak%2C%20signalling%20Noah%20that%20the%20waters%20have%20receded%2C%20and%20living%20creatures%20can%20finally%20come%20out%20of%20the%20ark%20and%20repopulate%20the%20earth.%20It%20symbolises%20the%20beginnings%20of%20life%20after%20deluge%20akin%20to%20life%20and%20growth%20emerging%20after%20the%20darkness%2C%20the%20earth%20becoming%20habitable%20and%20peaceful%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20450px)%2085vw%2C%20450px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152019%2Funnamed-3-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152019%2Funnamed-3-1.jpg%20450w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152019%2Funnamed-3-1-167x300.jpg%20167w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684696%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%2016th%20century%20Mughal%20miniature%20by%20Miskina%2C%20an%20artist%20in%20Akbar%E2%80%99s%20court%2C%20of%20the%20Noah%E2%80%99s%20ark%2C%20Prophet%20Nuh%20in%20Islam%2C%20National%20Museum%20of%20Asian%20Art%2C%20Smithsonian%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOlives%20have%20always%20been%20a%20part%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2021%2F10%2F14%2Finfographic-palestines-olive-industry%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPalestinian%20economic%20trade%20and%20sustenance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20besides%20being%20a%20shared%20cultural%20entity.%20They%20continue%20to%20be%20so%20in%20both%20Palestinian%20and%20Israeli%20societies.%20The%20cultivators%20of%20olives%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20farmers%20who%20owned%20most%20of%20the%20lands%20with%20olive-grooves%20until%201947%2C%20had%20always%20shared%20an%20extended%20kinship%20with%20the%20trees%20%E2%80%93%20some%20of%20trees%20being%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20years%20in%20age%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20so%20much%20so%20that%20they%20look%20at%20them%20as%20no%20less%20than%20their%20kins%2C%20as%20one%20of%20their%20own%2C%20as%20families%20with%20whom%20they%20share%20an%20ancestral%20relation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20the%20socio-cultural%20investment%20where%20harvesting%20months%20have%20always%20been%20celebrated%20as%20festivities%2C%20with%20families%20taking%20time%20off%20work%20and%20gathering%20to%20pick%20olives%20together%20for%20weeks.%20The%20emotional%20and%20sentimental%20investment%20in%20olive-trees%20became%20more%20pronounced%20as%20the%20settler%20attacks%20on%20farmers%20increased%20manifold%20in%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fdiscover%2Ftree-trust-meet-man-guarding-palestines-oldest-olive-tree%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOlive-trees%2C%20since%20then%20have%20become%20symbol%20of%20resilience%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20attachment%20and%20belonging%2C%20one%20without%20which%20the%20idea%20of%20home%2Fhomeland%20cannot%20be%20complete.%20People%20have%20been%20fighting%20legal%20battles%20to%20get%20a%20permit%20issued%20in%20their%20names%20so%20that%20they%20can%20access%20land%20that%20belongs%20to%20them%20but%20one%20that%20lay%20inaccessible%20by%20separation%20walls%2C%20settler%20only%20roads%2C%20proximity%20with%20the%20settlements%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20planting%2C%20grooming%20and%20harvesting%20season%20that%20once%20was%20a%20source%20of%20shared%20cultural%20and%20historic%20importance%20has%20now%20become%20a%20source%20of%20anxiety.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20has%20led%20to%20many%20social%20organizations%20around%20the%20world%2C%20and%20in%20Israel%20and%20West%20bank%2C%20getting%20involved%20through%20volunteering.%20People%20from%20around%20the%20world%20come%20during%20the%20harvest%20season%20and%20stay%20with%20the%20families%20for%20weeks%2C%20picking%20olives%20and%20paying%20%E2%80%98witness%E2%80%99%20to%20any%20sort%20of%20settler%20violence%20and%20intimidation%20that%20Palestinians%20farmers%20are%20no%20now%20highly%20exposed%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmidst%20all%20of%20this%2C%20olives%20continue%20to%20thrive%20as%20a%20cultural%20symbol%20of%20three%20people%20who%20belong%20to%20one%20land%20and%20have%20shared%20the%20socio-cultural%20and%20religious%20significance%20of%20trees%20that%20are%20rendered%20blessed%20in%20each%20of%20their%20scriptures.%20It%20is%2C%20as%20if%2C%20the%20olive%20trees%20have%20stood%20in%20testimony%20to%20shared%20multi-religious%20co-existence%20as%20three%20religions%20and%20a%20shared%20civilisation%20flourished%20in%20the%20region%20in%20the%20ancient%2C%20Byzantine%20and%20Roman%20times%20till%20that%20of%20Ottomans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20across%20religions%20have%20a%20bond%20with%20them%2C%20both%20religious%20and%20psychological%2C%20and%20the%20cultural%20economic%20value%20of%20these%20trees%20continues%20to%20shape%20and%20inform%20people%20both%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20of%20a%20past%20that%20nurtured%20natural%20and%20human%2C%20material%20and%20immaterial%20life%20equally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20continuing%20to%20engage%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20vs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethem%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ediscourse%2C%20the%20settler%20violence%20is%20particularly%20harming%20these%20trees%20and%20causing%20a%20forced%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20and%20is%20completely%20blind%20to%20their%20own%20history%20that%20regards%20olive%20trees%20as%20sacred.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForms%20of%20eco-cultural%20attachments%20are%20widely%20found%20especially%20in%20displaced%20populations%20who%20are%20made%20to%20live%20like%20refugees%20in%20and%20outside%20their%20homelands.%20The%20material%20concrete%20stories%20of%20land%2C%20home%2C%20fields%2C%20rivers%2C%20wind%2C%20clothes%2C%20food%2C%20become%20bed-time%20stories%20that%20each%20new%20generation%20grows%20up%20with.%20The%20idea%20of%20home%2C%20though%20lost%2C%20is%20not%20forgotten%20but%20instead%20becomes%20stronger%20and%20alive%20as%20years%20pass%20by.%20Nowhere%20has%20this%20been%20more%20profound%20than%20in%20the%20post-colonial%20Partition%20and%20separation%20stories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152710%2FPalestinian_children_on_rooftop.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152710%2FPalestinian_children_on_rooftop.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152710%2FPalestinian_children_on_rooftop-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14152710%2FPalestinian_children_on_rooftop-1024x681.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684700%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPalestinian%20children%20on%20rooftop.%20Photo%3A%20Justin%20McIntosh%2C%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%2C%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20children%20of%20Partition%20in%20South%20Asia%20have%20been%20living%20with%20these%20every%20day%2C%20especially%20those%20of%20us%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20families%20of%20the%20displaced.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.uvic.ca%2Findex.php%2Fbigreview%2Farticle%2Fview%2F20994%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EStories%20in%20my%20own%20life%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20been%20shaping%20my%20idea%20of%20home%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20now.%20The%20sense%20of%20belonging%20gets%20rooted%20firmly%20in%20the%20ecological%2C%20cultural%20and%20material%20belongings%2C%20and%20myths%2C%20folktales%20and%20scriptural%20stories%2C%20all%20have%20a%20profound%20role%20in%20shaping%20attachments%20across%20borders%20and%20barriers%2C%20unnaturally%20and%20artificially%20created%20to%20keep%20people%20separated.%20The%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%98a%20sentient%20being%E2%80%99%20is%20rooted%20in%20%E2%80%98an%20eco-cultural%20being%E2%80%99%20as%20much%20as%20it%20is%20rooted%20in%20other%20identity%20markers%20and%20expressions%20such%20as%20language%2C%20religion%2C%20gender%2C%20territory%20etc.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20have%20been%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20so%20much%20violence%2C%20the%20trees%20have%20always%20been%20their%20children%2C%20a%20part%20of%20their%20everyday%20lives.%20So%20much%20so%20that%20it%20shapes%20not%20only%20their%20idea%20of%20home%2C%20but%20also%20their%20idea%20of%20resistance.%20Proses%20and%20poetry%20continue%20to%20mention%20these%20trees%2C%20and%20it%20is%20important%20to%20revisit%20one%20of%20the%20most%20highly%20regarded%20poets%20and%20writers%2C%20Mahmoud%20Darwish%2C%20and%20his%20poem%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Second%20Olive%20Tree%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20poem%20is%20especially%20relevant%20in%20times%20such%20as%20these%2C%20as%20it%20symbolises%20rootedness%20in%20the%20land%20Palestinians%20call%20home%2C%20even%20in%20times%20of%20violent%20upheaval.%20Like%20life%2C%20the%20second%20olive%20tree%20in%20Darwish%E2%80%99s%20poem%20is%20the%20second%20child%2C%20the%20continued%20progeny%2C%20generational%20lineage%2C%20that%20refuses%20to%20die%20or%20vanish%20for%20the%20face%20of%20their%20beloved%20homeland%2C%20even%20when%20subjected%20to%20savagery%20and%20incomprehensible%20violence.%20Below%2C%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farablit.org%2F2022%2F03%2F30%2Fa-poem-for-land-day-mahmoud-darwishs-the-second-olive-tree%2F%5C%22%3EEnglish%20translation%20of%20the%20poem%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Marilyn%20Hacker%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Second%20Olive%20Tree%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20olive%20tree%20does%20not%20weep%20and%20does%20not%20laugh.%20The%20olive%20tree%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIs%20the%20hillside%E2%80%99s%20modest%20lady.%20Shadow%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECovers%20her%20single%20leg%2C%20and%20she%20will%20not%20take%20her%20leaves%20off%20in%20front%20of%20the%20storm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStanding%2C%20she%20is%20seated%2C%20and%20seated%2C%20standing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20lives%20as%20a%20friendly%20sister%20of%20eternity%2C%20neighbour%20of%20time%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20helps%20her%20stock%20her%20luminous%20oil%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForget%20the%20invaders%E2%80%99%20names%2C%20except%20the%20Romans%2C%20who%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECoexisted%20with%20her%2C%20and%20borrowed%20some%20of%20her%20branches%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20weave%20wreaths.%20They%20did%20not%20treat%20her%20as%20a%20prisoner%20of%20war%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20as%20a%20venerable%20grandmother%2C%20before%20whose%20calm%20dignity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESwords%20shatter.%20In%20her%20reticent%20silver-green%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EColor%20hesitates%20to%20say%20what%20it%20thinks%2C%20and%20to%20look%20at%20what%20is%20behind%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20portrait%2C%20for%20the%20olive%20tree%20is%20neither%20green%20nor%20silver.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20olive%20tree%20is%20the%20color%20of%20peace%2C%20if%20peace%20needed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20color.%20No%20one%20says%20to%20the%20olive%20tree%3A%20How%20beautiful%20you%20are!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%3A%20How%20noble%20and%20how%20splendid!%20And%20she%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20who%20teaches%20soldiers%20to%20lay%20down%20their%20rifles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20re-educates%20them%20in%20tenderness%20and%20humility%3A%20Go%20home%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20light%20your%20lamps%20with%20my%20oil!%20But%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20soldiers%2C%20these%20modern%20soldiers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesiege%20her%20with%20bulldozers%20and%20uproot%20her%20from%20her%20lineage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20earth.%20They%20vanquished%20our%20grandmother%20who%20foundered%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20branches%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20her%20roots%20in%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20did%20not%20weep%20or%20cry%20out.%C2%A0%C2%A0But%20one%20of%20her%20grandsons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWho%20witnessed%20the%20execution%20threw%20a%20stone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20a%20soldier%2C%20and%20he%20was%20martyred%20with%20her.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20victorious%20soldiers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20gone%20on%20their%20way%2C%20we%20buried%20him%20there%2C%20in%20that%20deep%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20cradle.%20And%20that%20is%20why%20we%20were%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESure%20that%20he%20would%20become%2C%20in%20a%20little%20while%2C%20an%20olive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETree%20%E2%80%93%20a%20thorny%20olive%20tree%20%E2%80%93%20and%20green!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EP.S%3A%20Olive-trees%20refuse%20to%20die.%20Farmers%20have%20been%20uprooting%20them%20from%20those%20parts%20of%20their%20fields%20that%20they%20are%20seldom%20allowed%20to%20access%2C%20and%20replanting%20them%20to%20the%20other.%20Many%20of%20these%20trees%20die%2C%20but%20most%20of%20them%20survive%20in%20the%20process.%20They%20grow%20profusely%2C%20with%20a%20thousand%20cuts%20(given%20their%20propagation%20through%20the%20techniques%20of%20cuts%20and%20grafts%20is%20widely%20used%20for%20olive-cultivation).%20One%20can%20cut%20the%20one-year-old%20younglings%20at%20a%20forty-five-degree%20angle%2C%20and%20they%20will%20survive.%20The%20fascinating%20part%20is%20to%20see%20them%20grow%20while%20being%20grafted%20together%2C%20a%20scion%20tightly%20fitted%20into%20a%20root-stock%2C%20glued%20to%20each%20other%2C%20as%20if%20providing%20life%20support%20to%20those%20who%20need%20it%20to%20further%20grow%20and%20sustain%20life.%20Sticking%20together%20as%20different%20children%20of%20one%20olive-branch%20in%20the%20region%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20collective%20growth.%20Perhaps%2C%20the%20time%20for%20the%20dove%20to%20fly%20and%20extend%20an%20olive-branch%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20all%20humankind%20is%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EMalvika%20Sharma%20is%20a%20post-doctoral%20researcher%20at%20Wesleyan%20University%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20US.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699957871000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F14153108%2FThe_Olive_Orchard_by_Vincent_van_Gogh_4991373613-e1699957838171.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-children-of-the-olive-branches%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Olive%20trees%20have%20become%20symbol%20of%20resilience%2C%20attachment%20and%20belonging%20for%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20one%20without%20which%20the%20idea%20of%20home%20and%20homeland%20cannot%20be%20complete.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-children-of-the-olive-branches%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22