%20admired%20the%20style%20of%20the%20women%20around%20me%2C%20but%20I%20missed%20the%20casual%20and%20comfortable%20outdoorsy%20clothes%20you%20see%20on%20the%20West%20Coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20favorite%20things%20about%20Houston%20were%20the%20radio%20stations%20%E2%80%94%20the%20rap%20and%20country%20stations%20were%20both%20really%20good.%20I%20also%20adored%20the%20Tex-Mex%20and%20barbecue%2C%20especially%20the%20brisket%20breakfast%20tacos%20(oatmeal%20and%20acai%20bowls%20are%20common%20breakfast%20favorites%20in%20Portland).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUltimately%2C%20my%20quality%20of%20life%20just%20wasn't%20the%20same%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Oregon%2C%20a%20drive%20to%20the%20coast%20can%20be%20a%20day%20trip.%20In%20Houston%2C%20going%20to%20Galveston%2C%20which%20is%20about%2050%20miles%20away%2C%20wasn't%20worth%20it%20unless%20we%20stayed%20for%20a%20weekend.%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20ski%20the%20mountains%20in%20Oregon%2C%20but%20I%20could%20at%20least%20visit%20and%20snowshoe%20there.%20There%20aren't%20any%20mountains%20like%20that%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20visited%20Houston's%20arboretum%20and%20city%20gardens%20in%20our%20free%20time%2C%20but%20they%20were%20paved%2C%20crowded%2C%20and%20hot.%20Even%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Portland%2C%20hikers%20can%20get%20lost%20alone%20in%20muddy%20forests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daily%20Houston%20commute%2C%20which%20could%20take%20me%20anywhere%20from%20one%20to%20three%20hours%20a%20day%20depending%20on%20my%20schedule%2C%20exhausted%20me.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20choosing%20a%20central%20location%20when%20I%20chose%20our%20apartment%2C%20but%20the%20scale%20of%20Houston%20was%20greater%20than%20I%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHousing%20is%20more%20expensive%20in%20Portland%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20planning%20the%20move%2C%20I%20kept%20my%20housing%20budget%20between%20%241%2C100%20and%20%241%2C200%20for%20a%20one-bedroom%20to%20abate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flifestyle-creep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20save%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Portland%2C%20our%20rent%20was%20moving%20closer%20to%20%241%2C400%20for%20smaller%20and%20smaller%20apartments%2C%20but%20I%20found%20a%20place%20in%20Houston%20on%20the%20cheaper%20end%20of%20my%20budget%20that%20offered%20more%20square%20footage%2C%20a%20saltwater%20pool%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20gated%20parking.%20I'd%20only%20had%20street%20parking%20in%20Portland%2C%20and%20apartments%20with%20garages%20charged%20between%20%24100%20and%20%24%20200%20a%20month%20for%20one%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20I%20got%20to%20Spring%2C%20I%20found%20that%20adjacent%20to%20my%20300-unit%20apartment%20complex%20was%20a%20farmhouse%20property%20with%20several%20(smelly)%20horses.%20And%20there%20was%20a%20FedEx%20warehouse%20across%20the%20street%2C%20complete%20with%2018-wheeler%20traffic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20explored%20the%20Houston%20housing%20market%20and%20was%20tempted%20by%20gorgeous%2C%20enormous%20houses%20with%20luxuries%20that%20aren't%20common%20in%20Oregon%2C%20such%20as%20guest%20suites%20and%20large%20laundry%20rooms.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F29-millennial-never-buy-house-how-spend-save-money-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhen%20you%20buy%20a%20house%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you're%20also%20buying%20into%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20commit%20to%20that%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20transportation%20budget%20increased%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20transportation%20budget%20went%20up%20in%20Houston.%20I%20think%20I%20saw%20one%20city%20bus%20the%20entire%20time%20I%20was%20there%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20you%20want%20to%20take%20a%20bike%20ride%2C%20you%20have%20to%20drive%20your%20bike%20somewhere%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biztrib.com%2Fnews%2Ffive-things-to-know-about-tolling-in-oregon%2Farticle_53d11202-f6e1-5768-9f37-7a1b63505999.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eno%20toll%20roads%20in%20Oregon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20known%20for%20being%20friendly%20for%20alternative%20transportation%20like%20scooters%2C%20bikes%2C%20and%20walking.%20In%20Texas%2C%20tolls%20cost%20me%20between%20%2480%20and%20%24120%20a%20month.%20Gas%20was%20cheaper%20than%20in%20Oregon%2C%20but%20I%20needed%20to%20buy%20three%20tanks%20a%20month%20instead%20of%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20had%20to%20buy%20a%20second%20vehicle%20so%20we%20both%20could%20commute%20in%20Houston.%20In%20Portland%2C%20we%20shared%20one%20car%20and%20two%20bikes%2C%20which%20we%20often%20used%20to%20get%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Houston%2C%20when%20we%20looked%20for%20something%20to%20do%20we%20could%20decide%20between%20buying%20tickets%20to%20things%20like%20rodeos%20or%20museums%2C%20eating%20out%20at%20franchise%20or%20five-star%20restaurants%2C%20and%20shopping.%20Oregon%20has%20fewer%20options%20for%20shopping%20but%20is%20much%20more%20suited%20for%20fun%20and%20affordable%20outdoor%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlthough%20my%20income%20increased%20with%20the%20move%2C%20I%20spent%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20couple%20poses%20at%20a%20winery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6552568058cf5fbccb959415%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJules%20and%20Marshall%20back%20in%20Portland.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jules%20Rogers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20higher%20salary%20was%20spent%20on%20a%20second%20car%2C%20gas%2C%20tolls%2C%20more%20expensive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usnews.com%2Finsurance%2Fauto%2Fcheap-car-insurance-texas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecar%20insur