%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20on%20November13%2C%20calling%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20end%20to%20the%20violence%20against%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20occupied%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%2C%20organised%20by%20translators%20Anna%20Gunin%20and%20Maya%20Chhabra%2C%20addressed%20the%20connection%20translators%20had%20with%20writers%20from%20Gaza%2C%20despite%20the%20strip%20being%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecut%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20by%20a%20constant%20blockade%20since%202007.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Palestinians%20who%20live%20%5Bin%20Gaza%5D%20cannot%20leave%20without%20exit%20permits%20from%20Israel%20or%20Egypt%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%20%E2%80%9CGaza%E2%80%99s%20airspace%20and%20sea%20border%20are%20both%20controlled%20by%20Israel.%20Yet%20writers%20from%20Gaza%20continue%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20tell%20the%20world%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20them.%20Sometimes%20they%20are%20killed%20just%20days%20or%20weeks%20after%20their%20words%20reach%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%20the%20translators%20watch%20%E2%80%9Cin%20horror%20as%20Israeli%20bombs%20fall%20on%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20citing%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2Fliveblog%2F2023%2F11%2F13%2Fisrael-hamas-war-live-gazas-two-largest-hospitals-shut-amid-nonstop-raids%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMore%2520than%252011%252C200%2520Palestinians%2520have%2Cstands%2520at%2520more%2520than%25201%252C200.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecurrent%20death%20toll%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20area%2C%20which%20now%20stands%20at%2011%2C200%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFaced%20with%20this%20carnage%2C%20the%20undersigned%20literary%20translators%20feel%20morally%20compelled%20to%20oppose%20the%20devaluation%20of%20Palestinian%20civilian%20lives%20and%20to%20call%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20said%20the%20urgency%20does%20not%20apply%20only%20to%20Gaza%2C%20but%20the%20West%20Bank%20as%20well.%20Since%20Oct.%207%2C%20Israeli%20forces%20have%20killed%20more%20than%20100%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20Israeli-occupied%20West%20Bank%2C%20which%20is%20not%20controlled%20by%20Hamas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSoldiers%20abuse%20detainees%3B%20extremist%20settlers%20attack%20Palestinian%20civilians%20with%20impunity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAn%20equitable%20resolution%20that%20ends%20the%20occupation%20and%20enables%20Palestinians%20and%20Israelis%20to%20live%20in%20peace%20and%20freedom%20seems%20as%20far%20away%20as%20ever.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20discouragement%20felt%20by%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20the%20statement%20said%20the%20group%20believes%20peace%20is%20possible%20and%20that%20it%20starts%20with%20protecting%20civilians.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20insist%20that%20Palestinian%20lives%20have%20equal%20value%20and%20that%20civilians%20must%20be%20protected%20at%20all%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20translators%20who%20signed%20the%20statement%20included%20International%20Booker%20Prize%20winners%20Jennifer%20Croft%2C%20Daisy%20Rockwell%20and%20Deborah%20Smith%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESusan%20Bernofsky%20and%20Antonia%20Lloyd-Jones%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20ended%20by%20asking%20other%20translators%20and%20professionals%20in%20the%20field%20to%20join%20them%20in%20calling%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire%20and%20lifting%20of%20the%20blockade%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20release%20of%20Israeli%20hostages%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20just%20peace%20that%20ends%20the%20current%20domin