21bd51c9c3218f482910e57fcc0e4bc884d6%257Ctwcon%255Es1_c10%26ref_url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fpib.gov.in%252FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%253FPRID%253D1976319%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20pay%20homage%20to%20Acharya%20JB%20Kripalani%20on%20his%20birth%20anniversary.%20He%20is%20widely%20respected%20as%20a%20true%20beacon%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20fight%20against%20colonialism.%20His%20tireless%20work%20to%20strengthen%20democracy%20and%20social%20equality%20has%20etched%20a%20permanent%20mark%20on%20our%20nation%E2%80%99s%20fabric.%20His%20life%20and%20work%20was%20always%20about%20upholding%20the%20values%20of%20liberty%20and%20justice.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20cannot%20help%20but%20marvel%20at%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20publicly%20praise%20historical%20personalities%20whose%20values%20stood%20in%20direct%20opposition%20to%20his%20own.%20Of%20course%2C%20it%20is%20also%20entirely%20possible%20that%20his%20lavish%20praise%20for%20Kripalani%20was%20a%20sly%20dig%20at%20Nehru%2C%20with%20whom%2C%20it%20is%20well%20known%2C%20Kripalani%20did%20not%20enjoy%20an%20easy%20equation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJeevatram%20Bhagwandas%20Kripalani%20%E2%80%93%20called%20%E2%80%98Acharya%E2%80%99%20because%20he%20was%20once%20the%20principal%20of%20Gujarat%20Vidyapith%20in%20Ahmedabad%20%E2%80%93%20worked%20closely%20with%20Gandhi%20during%20the%20Champaran%20Satyagraha%2C%20Dandi%20March%20and%20the%20Quit%20India%20movement.%20He%20not%20only%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20at%20the%20crucial%20time%20of%20Independence%2C%20but%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20and%20a%20subsequent%20four-time%20MP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EJ.B.%20Kripalani%20also%20happened%20to%20be%20a%20distant%20cousin%20and%20close%20friend%20of%20my%20own%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enana%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(maternal%20grandfather).%20The%20two%20grew%20up%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20Sindh%2C%20on%20the%20same%20lane%2C%20Kripalani%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eghitti%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20it%20was%20called.%20After%20my%20grandfather%20moved%20to%20Kolkata%20in%201918%2C%20Acharya%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20come%20and%20stay%20with%20him%20whenever%20he%20visited%20the%20city.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20279px)%2085vw%2C%20279px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F02145454%2FAcharya_Kripalani_1989_stamp_of_India-206x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22279%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F02145454%2FAcharya_Kripalani_1989_stamp_of_India-206x300.jpg%20206w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F02145454%2FAcharya_Kripalani_1989_stamp_of_India.jpg%20666w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-579105%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22406%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%201989%20stamp%20of%20J.B.%20Kripalani.%20Photo%3A%20India%20Post%2C%20GoI%2F%20GODL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlways%20dressed%20in%20a%20white%2C%20khadi%20dhoti-kurta%2C%20Acharya%20was%20fun%20to%20be%20around.%20He%20loved%20to%20play%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echaupar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20an%20ancient%20cross%20and%20circle%20board%20game%2C%20with%20my%20grandfather.%20Politicians%20of%20various%20persuasions%20would%20come%20home%20to%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Enana%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20house%20on%20Chowringhee%20Lane%20to%20meet%20Acharya%20who%2C%20while%20not%20stopping%20his%20game%20on%20their%20account%2C%20would%20nonetheless%20carry%20on%20conversations%20with%20them.%20He%20would%2C%20however%2C%20swear%20loudly%20at%20the%20dice%20each%20time%20they%20failed%20to%20deliver%20the%20desired%201%20plus%2012%2C%20or%20another%20magic%20figure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKripalani%20made%20no%20secret%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20and%20Nehru%20did%20not%20see%20eye%20to%20eye%20on%20many%20issues%2C%20the%20main%20ones%20being%20the%20division%20of%20power%20between%20the%20Congress%20party%20and%20the%20elected%20government%2C%20and%20the%20debate%20over%20a%20rural-centric%20economy%20versus%20an%20urban-centric%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20India%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%20the%20Indo-China%20war%20of%201962%2C%20he%20moved%20an%20unsuccessful%20no-confidence%20motion%20against%20Nehru.%20Of%20that%20particular%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20grandson%20Gopalkrishna%20Gandhi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-purest-kind-remembering-acharya-j-b-kripalani%2Fcid%2F1856705%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CKripalani%20brought%20into%20the%20House%20a%20large%20bundle%20of%20telegrams%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20India%20in%20support.%20They%20poured%20down%20from%20his%20quivering%20hands%20as%20he%20moved%20his%20resolution%20charging%20Nehru%20with%20authoritarianism.%20Nehru%20sat%20through%20and%20heard%20the%20excoriation%20with%20a%20smile%2C%20not%20of%20condescension%20but%20of%20respect%20for%20the%20veteran%20and%20his%20veteran%20right.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20noting%2C%20that%20at%20no%20point%20in%20his%20political%20career%20did%20his%20opposition%20to%20Nehru%20ever%20turn%20into%20personal%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ead%20hominem%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eattacks.%20Nor%20did%20he%20bad%20mouth%20Nehru%20to%20my%20grandfather%20or%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20us.%20It%20is%20also%20worth%20remembering%20that%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20Kripalani%E2%80%99s%20unrelenting%20criticisms%20remained%20dignified%20no%20matter%20how%20heated%20their%20debates%20and%20arguments%20became%2C%20both%20within%20the%20and%20outside%20the%20parliament.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20not%20only%20did%20Nehru%20back%20Kripalani%E2%80%99s%20bid%20for%20the%20Congress%20presidency%20against%20conservative%20Purushottam%20Das%20Tandon%20in%201950%2C%20he%20even%20offered%20Kripalani%20a%20place%20in%20the%20Union%20cabinet%20as%20well%20as%20a%20governorship.%20But%20Kripalani%2C%20very%20much%20his%20own%20man%2C%20turned%20down%20both%20offers%20and%20went%20on%20to%20eventually%20become%20an%20independent%20MP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F26112613%2FDnGmQuyU4AEnQxB.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F26112613%2FDnGmQuyU4AEnQxB.jpeg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F26112613%2FDnGmQuyU4AEnQxB-300x200.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-637702%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22425%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E1938%2C%20Bombay.%20Subhas%20C.%20Bose%20addresses%20the%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20National%20Planning%20committee.%20Others%20present%20include%20Chairman%20Nehru%2C%20Patel%2C%20Kripalani%2C%20Meghnad%20Saha%2C%20M.%20Visveswaraiah.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40Advaidism%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20courtesy%2C%20Nehru%20also%20left%20Kripalani%E2%80%99s%20constituency%20uncontested%20by%20the%20Congress%2C%20till%20Kripalani%20insisted%20on%20a%20fight%20and%20ended%20up%20losing%20the%20North%20Bombay%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20seat%20in%201962%20to%20Krishna%20Menon.%20(Kripalani%2C%20incidentally%2C%20was%20given%20a%20front%20seat%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20in%20parliament%20as%20a%20mark%20of%20respect%2C%20even%20though%20independent%20MPs%20are%20not%20given%20this%20privilege.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20when%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBlitz%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eweekly%20called%20Kripalani%20%E2%80%9Ccripple-loony%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20admonished%20its%20Chief%20Editor%2C%20Russi%20Karanjia%20for%20%E2%80%9Cdenigrating%20and%20defaming%20a%20member%20of%20parliament.%E2%80%9D%20This%2C%20despite%20Karanjia%E2%80%99s%20closeness%20to%20Nehru.%C2%A0A%20far%20cry%2C%20indeed%2C%20from%20the%20current%20government%20that%20uses%20both%20print%20and%20electronic%20media%20to%20punish%20dissenters%20and%20political%20opponents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Nehru%20passed%20away%20in%201964%2C%20Kripalani%20wrote%20an%20article%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20Nehru%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20July%20edition%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Economic%20Weekly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20year%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20293px)%2085vw%2C%20293px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F18111704%2FA52-297328-293x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22293%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F18111704%2FA52-297328-293x300.jpg%20293w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F18111704%2FA52-297328.jpg%20375w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-614335%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGandhi%20talking%20with%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20on%20his%2077th%20birthday.%20New%20Delhi.%20India.%20October%202%2C%201946.%20%C2%A9%20Dinodia%20Photos%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CIndia%20was%20almost%20the%20only%20colonial%20country%20which%20had%20given%20a%20determined%20fight%20to%20British%20imperialism%20and%20in%20the%20process%20made%20conspicuous%20sacrifices.%20Its%20leaders%20trained%20under%20Gandhiji%20had%20fully%20imbibed%20the%20best%20British%20traditions%20of%20humanism%2C%20liberalism%20and%20democracy%E2%80%A6%20these%20well-established%20traditions%20were%20kept%20up%20by%20Jawaharlal.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENehru%20and%20Kripalani%E2%80%99s%20contentious%20and%20prickly%2C%20yet%20ultimately%20respectful%20relationship%2C%20underlines%20one%20of%20the%20great%20lacunae%20of%20current%20Indian%20parliamentary%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20the%20ability%20to%20debate%20without%20denigrating%2C%20and%20criticise%20without%20stooping%20to%20use%20the%20kind%20of%20language%20that%20someone%20like%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20MP%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20gotten%20away%20with.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20good%20at%20paying%20verbal%20homage%20to%20the%20departed%20greats%20on%20social%20media.%20It%20is%20perhaps%20too%20much%20to%20expect%20much%20else%20from%20him.%20Let%20us%20hope%20that%20the%20next%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20see%20those%20who%2C%20like%20Nehru%20and%20Kripalani%2C%20can%20actually%20revive%20our%20great%20democratic%20traditions%20of%20discussion%2C%20debate%2C%20and%20dissent%2C%20and%20do%20justice%20to%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERohit%20Kumar%20is%20an%20educator%2C%20author%2C%20and%20independent%20journalist%2C%20a