Cem%3EOld%20World%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Photo%20provided%20by%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20you%20first%20read%20%3Cem%3EOld%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Aleksei%20Arbuzov%3F%20What%20was%20your%20reaction%20to%20it%20and%20how%20did%20you%20prepare%20for%20your%20character%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20seen%20the%20Kendals%20(Geoffrey%20and%20Laura)%20do%20%3Cem%3EOld%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%20many%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20I%20had%20read%20the%20script%20before.%20When%20Naseer%20decided%20to%20do%20it%2C%20I%20reread%20the%20script%20and%20found%20that%20it%20had%20great%20possibilities.%20It%20spoke%20to%20me%20at%20this%20stage%20in%20my%20life%20very%20clearly.%20I%20found%20many%20resonances%20with%20the%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArghya%20Lahiri%2C%20the%20director%2C%20and%20I%20started%20reading%20the%20play%20together%20in%20April.%20We%20started%20working%20on%20it%20in%20August%2C%20so%20we%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20the%20script.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20I%20approached%20this%20script%20and%20the%20character%20is%20the%20same%20as%20every%20other%20time%2C%20which%20is%20by%20reading%20the%20script%20as%20many%20times%20as%20I%20can%2C%20and%20imagining%20what%20I%20would%20be%20if%20I%20were%20in%20this%20situation%20and%20I%20was%20this%20person.%20It%20helps%20me%20create%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20character%20in%20my%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20process%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20reading%2C%20practice%2C%20and%20a%20large%20dollop%20of%20imagination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20difficult%20has%20it%20been%20to%20work%20together%20in%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EOld%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20piece%20that%20is%20vulnerable%20and%20addresses%20the%20complexities%20of%20old%20age%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20difficult%20at%20all%20and%20it%20has%20been%20a%20pleasure%20all%20over%20again.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us%20after%20a%20long%20time%2C%20since%20%3Cem%3EDear%20Liar.%3C%2Fem%3E%20So%2C%20there%20is%20a%20special%20feeling%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20piece%2C%20%3Cem%3EOld%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20something%20we%20have%20thought%20about%20a%20lot%20and%20experienced%20some%20of%20the%20things%20that%20have%20been%20spoken%20about%20in%20the%20play.%20It%20resonates%20with%20me%20as%20I%20grow%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20positive%20take%20on%20this%20issue.%20There%20is%20no%20moaning%20and%20groaning.%20Most%20Indian%20plays%20on%20old%20age%20tend%20to%20be%20extremely%20sentimental%20and%20make%20old%20people%20into%20poor%20old%20things.%20This%20play%20doesn%E2%80%99t.%20It%20shows%20them%20as%20vibrant%20human%20beings%20with%20different%20approaches%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20has%20been%20a%20while%20since%20you%20directed%20a%20play.%20What%20keeps%20you%20away%20from%20directing%20for%20the%20stage%3F%20What%20about%20film%2C%20is%20that%20something%20you%20would%20want%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20it%20has%20been%20quite%20a%20while.%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20found%20anything%20I%20would%20like%20to%20direct.%20The%20last%20two%20experiences%20I%20had%20weren%E2%80%99t%20satisfactory%20and%20I%20need%20to%20brush%20up%20my%20skills%20before%20I%20try%20it%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20I%20will%20try%20directing%20a%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20your%20comments%20on%20the%20current%20state%20of%20contemporary%20theatre%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20and%20India%3F%20What%20are%20some%20of%20the%20significant%20changes%20you%20see%20today%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheatre%20is%20going%20through%20a%20rather%20challenging%20phase.%20It%20may%20not%20appear%20so%20when%20you%20are%20at%20Prithvi%20Theatre.%20Elsewhere%2C%20it%20is%20a%20problem%2C%20particularly%20with%20the%20bigger%20theatre%20groups.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20as%20much%20of%20a%20commercially%20viable%20proposition%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20Television%20and%20OTT%20have%20eaten%20into%20the%20audiences.%20Also%2C%20the%20distances%20and%20commute%20have%20made%20it%20more%20difficult.%20Not%20to%20mention%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20lockdown%20that%20pulled%20the%20rug%20from%20under%20our%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it%20has%20spawned%20all%20sorts%20of%20theatrical%20activity%20and%20people%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20imagine%20performance%20in%20different%20ways%20and%20not%20just%20in%20a%20physical%20theatre.%20They%20are%20productions%20that%20could%20be%20done%20in%20someone%E2%80%99s%20drawing%20room%2C%20in%20a%20small%20theatre%20space%2C%20in%20a%20black%20box%2C%20on%20the%20street%2C%20or%20in%20a%20garden.%20This%20flexibility%20of%20ideas%20and%20these%20imaginative%20theatre%20techniques%20have%20been%20a%20source%20of%20hope%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20theatre%20will%20find%20different%20forms%20now%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20fulfil%20its%20real%20purpose%2C%20which%20is%20to%20have%20contact%20with%20each%20member%20of%20the%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20there%20any%20recent%20theatre%20productions%20that%20you%20have%20watched%20and%20enjoyed%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20enjoyed%20%3Cem%3ESangeet%20Bari%3C%2Fem%3E%20(written%20by%20Bhushan%20Korgaonkar%20and%20directed%20by%20Savitri%20Medhatul)%20very%20much.%20Apart%20from%20being%20informative%2C%20it%20was%20entertaining%20and%20beautiful%20to%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20equally%20loved%20%3Cem%3EJo%20Dooba%20So%20Paar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(written%20by%20Ajitesh%20Gupta%2C%20and%20directed%20by%20Ajitesh%20Gupta%20and%20Mohit%20Agarwal)%2C%20based%20on%20the%20life%20of%20Amir%20Khusrau.%20The%20energy%20of%20the%20performers%2C%20how%20the%20story%20was%20told%2C%20and%20the%20absolute%20magic%20of%20the%20singing.%20I%20enjoyed%20everything%